column12: Mechanical engineering cutting device
column13: The utility model discloses a mechanical engineering cutting device which comprises a base, a workbench is fixedly connected to the upper surface of the front end of the base, a flow guide groove is formed below the workbench, the upper surface of the middle of the base is fixedly connected to the lower end of a stand column, and the upper end of the stand column is connected to the lower surface of a support plate through a shaft. A motor is fixedly installed at one end of the support plate, a protective cover is fixedly installed on the side face of the other end of the support plate, a water tank is arranged below the flow guide groove and fixedly connected to the side face of the base, a filter is arranged in the middle of the water tank, the rear end of the water tank communicates with a water tank, and a cooling pipe is connected to the outer side of the motor in a nested mode. And one end of the cooling pipe is connected with the upper end of the conveying pipe. According to the mechanical engineering cutting device, dust and chippings can be conveniently prevented from splashing in the metal material cutting process, sectional materials in the cutting process can be cooled, a motor in work can be cooled, and therefore the working time of equipment is prolonged.
column15: YANG CHAOFAN;;YANG MING;;FU KAI

column12: Mechanical designing and machining part
column13: The utility model discloses a mechanical design processing part, which mainly comprises a reference seat, a clamping seat and a clamping block, two sides of the reference seat are respectively provided with a first screw hole, the middle part of the reference seat is meshed with a screw rod, the outer side end of the screw rod is fixedly provided with a butterfly head rotating handle, the inner side end of the screw rod is provided with a second screw hole, and the first screw hole and the second screw hole are communicated. A rotating head is fixed to the end of the inner side of the screw in a matched mode and connected with a clamping base through a bearing in a matched mode, a clamping block is fixed to the inner side of the clamping base, counterbores are formed in the two sides of the clamping block, and a rubber pad is fixed to the inner side of the clamping block. The clamping and fixing device is a mechanical design machining part, is mainly used for clamping and fixing the mechanical machining part, is simple in overall structure, low in machining cost, good in use flexibility, capable of clamping and fixing workpieces of different sizes or different shapes, and low in later maintenance and replacement cost.

column12: Low-Resistance Contact Plugs and Method Forming Same
column13: A method includes forming a first and a second contact opening to reveal a first and a second source/drain region, respectively, forming a mask layer having a first and a second portion in the first and the second contact openings, respectively, forming a first and a second sacrificial ILD in the first and the second contact openings, respectively, removing the first sacrificial ILD from the first contact opening, filling a filler in the first contact opening, and etching the second sacrificial ILD. The filler protects the first portion of the mask layer from being etched. An ILD is formed in the second contact opening and on the second portion of the mask layer. The filler and the first portion of the mask layer are removed using a wet etch to reveal the first contact opening. A contact plug is formed in the first contact opening.

column12: Verfahren zur Herstellung eines Kontaktsteckers mit niedrigem Widerstand
column13: Ein Verfahren umfasst das Ausbilden einer ersten und einer zweiten Kontaktöffnung, um einen ersten bzw. einen zweiten Source/Drain-Bereich freizulegen, das Ausbilden einer Maskenschicht mit einem ersten und einem zweiten Abschnitt in der ersten bzw. der zweiten Kontaktöffnung, das Ausbilden eines ersten und eines zweiten Opfer-ILDs in der ersten bzw. der zweiten Kontaktöffnung, das Entfernen des ersten Opfer-ILDs von der ersten Kontaktöffnung, das Füllen eines Füllstoffs in die erste Kontaktöffnung und das Ätzen des zweiten Opfer-ILDs. Der Füllstoff schützt den ersten Abschnitt der Maskenschicht vor Ätzen. Ein ILD wird in der zweiten Kontaktöffnung und auf dem zweiten Abschnitt der Maskenschicht ausgebildet. Der Füllstoff und der erste Teil der Maskenschicht werden unter Verwendung eines Nassätzens entfernt, um die erste Kontaktöffnung freizulegen. Ein Kontaktstecker wird in der ersten Kontaktöffnung ausgebildet. ()

column12: Wire coiling machine facilitating discharging
column13: The invention discloses a wire coiling machine facilitating discharging, and relates to the technical field of wire coiling machines. The wire coiling machine facilitating discharging comprises two supports used for supporting a wire coil and rotating mechanisms used for rotating the wire coil. The wire coil comprises a bobbin, rolling rings located at the two ends of the bobbin and a plurality of connecting rods located between the rolling rings and the bobbin, and the supports are provided with positioning heads used for being inserted into the end of the bobbin and driving mechanisms used for driving the positioning heads. One ends of the rotating mechanisms are rotationally connected to first telescopic pieces on the supports, second telescopic pieces located at the ends, away from the supports, of the first telescopic pieces and used for stirring the connecting rods, and rotating machines used for rotating the first telescopic pieces. According to the wire coiling machine facilitating discharging, loading and unloading of the wire coil are labor-saving.

column12: Automatic point target device of mass spectrometer
column13: The utility model discloses an automatic target pointing device of a mass spectrometer. The automatic target pointing device comprises a sample pointing table; the support is arranged on the sample application table and provided with a horizontal cross beam, a mechanical arm is arranged on the cross beam, a pipettor is arranged at the lower end of the mechanical arm, and a power pump is arranged at the upper end of the mechanical arm; the constant-temperature assembly comprises a heat conduction plate and a PTC heating piece, the PTC heating piece is arranged in the heat conduction plate, anda rectangular groove is formed in the heat conduction plate; the vacuum shell is provided with a vacuum sucking pump which is communicated with the vacuum shell; accurate temperature control (18-60 DEG C) in the device can be realized, the sample application volume and the sample application position are accurately controlled after a sample is sucked through the movement of the mechanical arm, andthe uniformity of sample application is improved. After sample application is finished, the vacuum pump is started, so that the liquid is quickly evaporated, the mass spectrum pretreatment time is shortened, automatic sample application of the mass spectrum sample target in a constant-temperature and dust-free environment can be realized, errors caused by manual operation are eliminated, and theonline pretreatment time of mass spectrum analysis is greatly prolonged.

column12: Preparation method of carbon material with three-dimensional network structure
column13: The invention provides a preparation method of a carbon material with a three-dimensional network structure. The preparation method specifically comprises the following steps: S1, synthesis of a precursor; S2, carbonization of the precursor. The invention provides a preparation method of a three-dimensional network structure carbon material, and the preparation method of the three-dimensional network structure carbon material utilizes organic amine small molecules to prepare the three-dimensional network structure carbon material to replace a common additive lignosulfonate and a two-dimensional sheet-shaped or granular carbon material of a lead-acid battery negative electrode. The problems that lignosulfonate is non-conductive and a two-dimensional sheet-shaped or granular carbon material cannot improve the porosity of a negative electrode are solved, so that the cycle performance of the battery working in a high-rate partial charge state is improved, and meanwhile, the carbon material prepared by the invention also has relatively high specific capacitance, and the specific capacity of the lead-acid battery can be improved.

column12: Nitrogen-doped high-specific-surface-area porous carbon material as well as preparation method and application thereof
column13: The invention provides a nitrogen-doped high-specific-surface-area porous carbon material, a preparation method thereof and application of the nitrogen-doped high-specific-surface-area porous carbon material in the aspect of supercapacitor energy storage. The method comprises the following steps of: based on the characteristic that an organic amine monomer can be polymerized in a high-temperature oxygen atmosphere, directly and uniformly mixing the organic amine monomer and an activating agent by adopting a physical method (such as dry grinding or ball milling) before polymerization, and then carrying out polymerization in an oxidizing atmosphere by utilizing a high-temperature tubular furnace, or carrying out polymerization reaction in the oxidizing atmosphere and then mixing the organic amine monomer with the activating agent; carrying out alkali activation in an inert atmosphere; and soaking in acid and water in sequence to finally obtain the nitrogen-doped porous carbon material with the average pore size of 0.5-10nm and the nitrogen adsorption determination specific surface area of 2000-4000 m<2>/g. The porous carbon material has excellent performance in the aspect of a supercapacitor. When lithium sulfate with the concentration of 1 mol/L serves as an electrolyte, an electrochemical stability window is 1.7 V vs RHE, and the scanning rate is 2 mV/s, the mass specific capacitance is 320 F/g.

column12: Drencher for animal husbandry and veterinary medicine
column13: The utility model discloses a drencher for animal husbandry veterinarians. The drencher comprises an injector, a sleeve arranged outside the injector in a sleeving mode and an opening expanding mechanism arranged at a medicine outlet of the injector. The opening supporting mechanism comprises a strip-shaped column, a medicine feeding pipe arranged in the middle of the strip-shaped column and used for guiding and feeding liquid medicine, two electromagnets arranged on the top face and the bottom face of the strip-shaped column respectively and two opening supporting pieces arranged above and below the strip-shaped column, and the opening supporting pieces are connected with the strip-shaped column through telescopic springs. And a groove for placing the telescopic spring is formed in the strip-shaped column. The drencher is provided with the auxiliary fixing mechanism, so that the head of an animal can be fixed in an auxiliary manner, and the drencher is prevented from falling off from the mouth of the animal to cause drenching failure due to struggling of the animal in the drenching process; the mouth of an animal can be supported through the mouth supporting mechanism, so that the mouth of the animal is opened, and drenching is facilitated.

column12: Pressure-loss and power-off interlocking protection device of steam sterilizer
column13: The utility model discloses a no-pressure power-off interlocking protection device of a steam sterilizer, and belongs to the technical field of steam sterilizer protection. The device comprises a compressed air input pipeline (5), the steam sterilizer is characterized in that the steam sterilizer is provided with an air storage tank (3), an inlet of the air storage tank (3) is connected with the compressed air input pipeline (5) through a pipeline, an air outlet of the air storage tank (3) is connected with an emptying valve (7), and the emptying valve (7) is simultaneously communicated with asterilization cavity (8) of the steam sterilizer. According to the pressure-loss and power-off interlocking protection device of the steam sterilizer, the air storage tank is arranged, so that air can be continuously provided for the sealing door after compressed air stops supplying air due to reasons, and high-temperature steam or high-temperature water in the sterilization cavity is prevented from leaking. And by arranging the one-way valve, gas output by the gas storage tank is prevented from reversely flowing in the condensed air input pipeline.

column12: Determination method and determination device for optimum capacity of inverter
column13: The invention provides a determination method and a determination device for optimum capacity of an inverter. The method comprises the steps of calculating direct current output quantity to obtain capacity of the inverter according to a meteorological condition, a geographic position, direct current installed capacity and relevant parameters of a photovoltaic component; performing disturbance by taking the capacity of the inverter as an initial value according to set step length; calculating alternating current side power output corresponding to the capacity of the inverter after the disturbance; establishing a difference value function between income and cost according to the capacity of the inverter, the price of the inverter, the alternating current side power output and a power tariff of a power grid; calculating a maximum value of the function; and taking the capacity of the inverter corresponding to the maximum value as the optimum capacity of the inverter. The method realizes profit maximization of a power grid system by determining the optimum capacity of the inverter.

column12: Preparation method and application of lead-carbon composite material
column13: The invention provides a preparation method and application of a lead-carbon composite material, and relates to the technical field of lead-carbon batteries. The preparation method of the lead-carbon composite material specifically comprises the following steps: S1, preparing a precursor; S2, obtaining the lead-carbon composite material; and S3, adding for use. According to the preparation method and application of the lead-carbon composite material provided by the invention, a negative electrode additive can be applied to a lead-carbon battery, so that the compatibility of carbon and lead can be well solved, the hydrogen evolution reaction of a negative electrode is effectively inhibited, and irreversible sulfation is relieved; and the high-rate partial charge state cycle performance is improved.

column12: Method of forming semiconductor device
column13: A method includes forming a gate structure on a substrate, forming a seal spacer covering a sidewall of the gate structure, forming a sacrificial spacer covering a sidewall of the seal spacer, forming source/drain regions sandwiching a channel region that is under the gate structure, and depositing a contact etch stop layer covering a sidewall of the sacrificial spacer. The method further includes removing the sacrificial spacer to form a trench, wherein the trench exposes a sidewall of the contact etch stop layer and the sidewall of the seal spacer, and depositing an inter-layer dielectric layer, wherein the inter-layer dielectric layer caps the trench, thereby defining an air gap inside the trench.

column12: Halbleitervorrichtung und Verfahren zu ihrer Herstellung
column13: In einem Verfahren zum Herstellen einer Halbleitervorrichtung wird eine Zwischenschichtdielektrikum (ILD)-Schicht über einer darunterliegenden Struktur ausgebildet. Die darunterliegende Struktur enthält Gate-Strukturen, die jeweils ein Metall-Gate und eine Kappisolierschicht, die über dem Metall-Gate angeordnet ist, aufweisen, epitaxiale Source/Drain-Schichten, die zwischen zwei benachbarten Gate-Strukturen angeordnet sind, und eine Ätzstoppschicht (Etching-Stop Layer, ESL), welche die epitaxialen Source/Drain-Schichten bedeckt. Eine Öffnung wird in der ILD-Schicht durch Ätzen ausgebildet. Eine dielektrische Füllschicht wird in der Öffnung ausgebildet. Mittels Nassätzen wird die ILD-Schicht entfernt, die über den epitaxialen Source/Drain-Schichten angeordnet ist. Die ESL, die auf den epitaxialen Source/Drain-Schichten angeordnet ist, wird entfernt, wodurch die epitaxialen Source/Drain-Schichten mindestens teilweise freigelegt werden. Ein leitfähiges Material wird über den frei liegenden epitaxialen Source/Drain-Schichten ausgebildet.
column15: LEE CHEN-MING;;YANG FU-KAI;;WANG MEI-YUN

column12: A semiconductor device and a method for fabricating the same
column13: In a method of manufacturing a semiconductor device, an interlayer dielectric (ILD) layer is formed over an underlying structure. The underlying structure includes gate structures, each having a metalgate and a cap insulating layer disposed over the metal gate, source/drain epitaxial layers disposed between two adjacent gate structures, and an etching-stop layer (ESL) covering the source/drain epitaxial layers. An opening is formed in the ILD layer by etching. A dielectric filling layer is formed in the opening. By using wet etching, the ILD layer disposed above the source/drain epitaxial layers is removed. The ESL disposed on the source/drain epitaxial layers is removed, thereby at least partially exposing the source/drain epitaxial layers. A conductive material is formed over the exposed source/drain epitaxial layers. The embodiment of the invention also relates to a semiconductor device.

column12: The growth method of size controlled in zno nanowires
column13: A diameter and length controlled method has been developed in ZnO nanowires. This approach exploits metal catalysts to control both the diameter and the length of ZnO nanowires and via growth time to control the length of the ZnO nanowires. The powder of ZnO was placed in the center of high temperature furnace, and silicon substrate with gold catalysts is located at the downstream end of a furnace with low temperature. The chamber was maintained at 100~200 Pa with a constant flow of pure Argon. In this experimental condition, the high temperature region ZnO powder was evaporated and the nanowires of ZnO were grow by reacting with gold catalysts at the downstream side of furnace. Therefore, different sizes of ZnO nanowires can be controled through the size of metal catalysts.And the length of the ZnO nanowires was increaced with increasing growth time.The diameter and length of ZnO nanowires controlled method can apply in selective growth of ZnO nanowires devices. This method also provides the industry with cheaper equipment and precise diameter and length of nanowires control in nanowires manufacture.

column12: Diagnosis method for diagnosing fault in operation of a motor fault and diagnosis device using the same
column13: A diagnosis method for diagnosing fault in operation of a motor fault and diagnosis device using the same is related to the diagnosis method including the following steps. Provide a vibrate sense module to obtain a vibration signal generated by the motor when the motor operates. Process the vibration signal to eliminate a noise signal in the vibration signal through performing a data preprocess. After the data preprocess, determine positions of a plurality of base frequency in the processed vibration signal through performing an analyzing process for a frequency spectrum of the vibration signal. Obtain a frequency spectrum feature from the frequency spectrum of the vibration signal based on the position of each base frequency. And, discriminate a type of fault of the motor by comparing the frequency spectrum feature with data in a fault feature frequency spectrum database.
column15: FU CHIA-LIN;;HSU CHEN-KAI;;HSU MING-HSIU

column12: DIAGNOSIS METHOD OF DEFECTS IN A MOTOR AND DIAGNOSIS DEVICE THEREOF
column13: A diagnosis method of defects in a motor and a diagnosis device thereof are described. A vibration sensing module can generate a vibration signal corresponding to a vibration of a motor during operation of the motor. Then, a data pre-processing procedure is performed to eliminate noises of the vibration signal. After the data pre-processing procedure, an analyzing procedure is performed to determine a first harmonic of spectrum features in the spectrum of the pre-processed vibration signal. And, other spectrum feature(s) is(/are) retrieved from the spectrum of the pre-processed vibration signal according to the first harmonic. Finally, a comparison procedure is performed with a defect spectrum feature database according to the retrieved spectrum features, so as to determine a defect type of the motor.
column15: FU CHIA-LIN;;HSU CHEN-KAI;;HSU MING-HSIU

column12: BATTERY USABLE TIME COMPUTATION
column13: Examples of computing devices for computing a usable time duration of an available power capacity of a battery of such computing devices are described herein. In an example, a computing device may include a battery, a processor, and a display device. The processor may determine a change in an available power capacity between a start and an end of a time interval· The processor may further compute a battery power consumption for the time interval based on the change. Further, the processor may compute a usable time duration of the available power capacity based on the battery power consumption and an available power capacity at the end of the time interval. The computed usable time duration is displayed by the display device.

column12: Control of bit-rate and packet duplication in a real-time media stream
column13: A method for controlling a real-time media stream between a sender and a receiver. The method includes streaming, from the sender, media packets over a network at a bit-rate, determining at the sender a loss-rate for the streamed media packets not received at the receiver. The sender optionally generates duplicate packets for a selected number of media packets and streams the duplicate packets over the network when the loss-rate is above a first loss-rate threshold, or varies the bit-rate of streaming the media packets over the network when the loss-rate is above a second loss-rate threshold.

column12: Image-type street light monitor, system and method
column13: Provided are an image-type street light monitor, system and method. The image-type street light monitor comprises an image capturing device, a control device and a transmission interface. The image capturing device shoots street lights to obtain an image screen; the control device comprises a recognition processor and a report processor, wherein the recognition processor carries out image processing on the image screen to determine whether each street light malfunctions, and the report processor generates a report data corresponding to the result of the recognition processor; the transmission interface transmits the report data to a management host. The effects of this invention comprise: easy installation of the street light monitor to reduce costs; using the image screen to determine whether a plurality of street lights malfunction at the same time to provide high recognition efficiency; and using the image as report data for the basis of repair or maintenance.

column12: UEFI VARIABLES GENERATION
column13: An electronic device may include a first non-volatile storage device having a first storage region, a second non-volatile storage device having a second storage region, and a processor. The processor may detect a modification to a data attribute, generate a first unified extensible firmware interface (UEFI) variable including modified data and previous data associated with the data attribute, and store the first UEFI variable in the first storage region via a first UEFI runtime service. Further, the processor may generate a second UEFI variable to include data indicating the modification to the data attribute and a counter to record boot count. Furthermore, the processor may store the second UEFI variable in the second storage region via the first UEFI runtime service. The processor selectively read, via a second UEFI runtime service, the modified data or previous data from the first storage region based on the second UEFI variable.

column12: Method for Forming Source/Drain Contacts
column13: Semiconductor devices and methods of forming the same are provided. In one embodiments, a semiconductor device includes an n-type transistor region and a p-type transistor region. The n-type transistor region includes a first gate stack, a first gate spacer over sidewalls of the first gate stack, an n-type epitaxial feature in a source/drain (S/D) region of the n-type transistor region, and a first metal silicide layer over the n-type epitaxial feature. The p-type transistor region includes a second gate stack, a second gate spacer over sidewalls of the second gate stack, a p-type epitaxial feature in an S/D region of the p-type transistor region, a dopant-containing implant layer over the p-type epitaxial feature, and a second metal silicide layer over the dopant-containing implant layer. The dopant-containing implant layer includes a metallic dopant.
column15: KOH SHAO-MING;;LEE CHEN-MING;;YANG FU-KAI;;WANG MEI-YUN

column12: Method for forming source/drain contacts
column13: Semiconductor devices and methods of forming the same are provided. In one embodiments, the method includes providing a structure that includes a substrate, a first gate structure and a second gate structure over the substrate, a first source/drain (S/D) feature comprising silicon adjacent to the first gate structure, a second S/D feature comprising silicon germanium (SiGe) adjacent to the second gate structure; and one or more dielectric layers over sidewalls of the first and second gate structures and over the first and second S/D features. The method further includes etching the one or more dielectric layers to form openings exposing the first and second S/D features, forming a masking layer over the first S/D feature, implanting gallium (Ga) into the second S/D feature while the masking layer is over the first S/D feature, removing the masking layer; and etching the first and second S/D features with an oxygen-atom-containing etchant.

According to the invented method, the application of an external voltage with a predetermined voltage value on the metal layer can alter potential of the metal layer and thus effectiveness of preventing metal layer corrosion and oxidation in manufacturing process can be achieved so that precision and yield of the subsequent processes can be increased.

column12: Improved method of thermal reflow process for conductive bump
column13: The present invention discloses an improved method of thermal reflow process for conductive bump, which is a method free of using flux by removing the oxide layer on the conductive bump. The first embodiment comprises loading the substrate containing the conductive bump on the thermal reflow furnace, and venting hydrogen gas into the thermal reflow furnace to remove the oxide layer on the conductive bump before proceeding the thermal reflow treatment; and then raising the temperature to proceed the thermal reflow treatment of conductive bump to form the conductive bump in a spherical structure. The second embodiment comprises placing the substrate containing the conductive bump on the heating plate of the plasma reaction chamber, venting CF gas into the plasma reaction chamber to remove the oxide layer on the conductive bump, and raising the temperature to proceed the thermal reflow treatment of conductive bump to form the conductive bump in a spherical structure.

The ring-shaped protrusion portion is disposed at the inner wall of the opening and has an inner diameter smaller than that of the wafer. In addition, the ring-shaped protrusion portion has the second scraping surface, which is approximately at the same level as the first scraping surface, and forms an integrated molding with the stencil body portion. column12: CONTACT RESISTANCE REDUCTION FOR TRANSISTORS
column13: The present invention relates to a contact resistance reduction for a transistor. A method comprises: a step of forming a gate stack; a step of growing a source/drain region on a side surface of the gate stack through an epitaxy; a step of forming a contact etching stop layer (CESL) on the source/drain region; a step of forming an interlayer dielectric body on the CESL; a step of etching the interlayer dielectric body and the CESL and forming a contact opening; and a step of etching the source/drain region to extend the contact opening into the source/drain region. The method additionally comprises a step of forming a metal layer extended into the contact opening. The horizontal part, vertical part, and corner parts of the metal layer have substantially uniform thicknesses. An annealing process is conducted to make the metal layer react with the source/drain region and form a source/drain silicide region. The contact opening is charged to form a source/drain contact plug.

column12: Frequency-converted frequency-modulated self-injection-locked radar
column13: A frequency-converted frequency-modulated self-injection-locked radar includes a self-injection-locked oscillator, a frequency-converted unit, an antenna unit, a demodulation unit and a computing unit. The self-injection-locked oscillator outputs an oscillated signal, the frequency-converted unit converts the oscillated signal into a frequency modulated continuous wave signal. The antenna unit transmits the frequency modulated continuous wave signal as a transmitted signal to an area, and receives a reflected signal reflected from the area as a received signal. The frequency-converted unit converts the received signal into an injection signal and injects the injection signal into the self-injection-locked oscillator. The demodulation unit demodulates the oscillated signal for obtaining an in-phase demodulated signal and a quadrature-phase demodulated signal. The computing unit computes a baseband signal by the in-phase demodulated signal and the quadrature-phase demodulated signal, and analyzes the spectrum of baseband signal to obtain a phase and a frequency of at least a tone of the frequency domain baseband signal. The computing unit determines the tone which corresponds to an object or a plurality objects by the phase and the frequency of the tone.

column12: Rubber-base flexible shielding material and preparation method thereof
column13: The invention provides a rubber-base flexible shielding material and a preparation process thereof. The shielding material uses radiation resistant styrene-butadiene rubber as a substrate. The substrate is improved in hardness and flexibility by an additive. Original gum plastication and banburying (or opening milling), oxidation crosslinking processing processes are used to produce. A mixing process is used to uniformly spread lead powder or boron carbide in the rubber substrate, which not only has excellent shielding performance but also super toughness as well as structural adaptability. The preparation process of the invention adopts an 'oxidation' method rather than a 'vulcanization' method in the molecule crosslinking reaction for preparing the flexible shielding material, and removes the sulphur in the rubber so as to enable the shielding material free from sulfur and suitable for use in the field of nuclear power.

column12: KONTAKTWIDERSTANDSREDUZIERUNG FÜR TRANSISTOREN
column13: Ein Verfahren umfasst Bilden eines Gatestapels, Aufwachsen eines Source/Drain-Bereichs auf einer Seite des Gatestapels durch Epitaxie, Abscheiden einer KontaktÄtzstoppschicht, CESL, über dem Source/Drain-Bereich, Abscheiden eines Zwischenschichtdielektrikums über der CESL, Ätzen des Zwischenschichtdielektrikums und der CESL, um eine Kontaktöffnung zu bilden, und Ätzen des Source/Drain-Bereichs, so dass sich die Kontaktöffnung in den Source/Drain-Bereich erstreckt. Das Verfahren umfasst ferner Abscheiden einer Metallschicht, die sich in die Kontaktöffnung erstreckt. Horizontale Abschnitte, vertikale Abschnitte und Eckabschnitte der Metallschicht weisen eine im Wesentlichen gleichmäßige Dicke auf. Ein Temperprozess wird durchgeführt, damit die Metallschicht mit dem Source/Drain-Bereich reagiert, um einen Source/Drain-Silizid-Bereich zu bilden. Die Kontaktöffnung wird gefüllt, um einen Source/Drain-Kontaktstopfen zu bilden.

column12: Continuous feeding device of vacuum process equipment.
column13: This invention relates to a continuous feeding device of vacuum process equipment. A main body connected with an air extracting device is provided respectively at two ends with a slot for the belt to be passingly provided, and a roller set having an upper and a lower roller is mounted therein for pinching the conveyor belt. Sealing mechanisms are provided between the roller set and the slots of the main body. The sealing mechanism is fixedly provided with a first sealing member at the inner side face of the main body's slot. Two laterals of the first sealing member are adjacent to a second sealing member, respectively , and the first sealing member and the second sealing member are respectively provided with an upper fitting part abutting against the peripheral face of the upper roller and a lower fitting part abutting against the peripheral face of the lower roller, capable of being installed at the input end and the out end of the vacuum process equipment to perform continuous conveyor belt. Accordingly, utilizing the sealing mechanisms of the main body, not only the gas flowing in from the slot can be effectively obstructed, but also a vacuum assisting chamber is formed in the main body, so as to facilitate the vacuum process equipment to perform vacuum processing of a material bag, and to replace or assemble each component easier, thereby achieve the practical benefits of enhancing the vacuum tightness and maintenance convenience of the overall equipment.

column12: Integrated Circuits Having Protruding Interconnect Conductors

In some examples, the method includes receiving a workpiece that includes an inter-level dielectric layer. A first contact that includes a fill material is formed that extends through the inter-level dielectric layer. The inter-level dielectric layer is recessed such that the fill material extends above a top surface of the inter-level dielectric layer. An etch-stop layer is formed on the inter-level dielectric layer such that the fill material of the first contact extends into the etch-stop layer. A second contact is formed extending through the etch-stop layer to couple to the first contact. In some such examples, the second contact physically contacts a top surface and a side surface of the first contact.

column12: Method of performing commercial transaction via bank wire transfer or remittance
column13: A method of performing commercial transaction via bank wire transfer or remittance is disclosed, which comprises the following steps: (A) after a merchant creating a transaction record of a consumer purchasing a product, a personal handheld device connecting to a transaction device, and the transaction device transmitting merchant information and the transaction record from the merchant to the personal handheld device; (B) the personal handheld device transmitting the merchant information and the transaction record to a consumer bank; (C) the consumer bank depositing a consumption amount into a merchant bank via wire transfer or remittance; (D) after completing the wire transfer or remittance, the consumer bank transmitting transaction completion information to at least one of the personal handheld device and the transaction device; and (E) after receiving the transaction completion information, informing the consumer or the merchant about transaction completion via an informing means.

column12: Deviation correcting device for mould pressing position of edition seam-free laser moulding press
column13: The utility model provides a deviation correcting device for mould pressing position of an edition seam-free laser moulding press, which belongs to the technical field of printing equipment and solves the problem that the relative positions of the two holographic image-text mother sets cannot be adjusted in the prior art. The deviation correcting device comprises a front transmission roller and a rear transmission roller, wherein the rear ends of the front transmission roller and the rear transmission roller are connected with a rear wall plate of a rack; the front ends of the front transmission roller and the rear transmission roller penetrate through a support and are arranged into concave grooves at the inner sides of a front left wall plate and a front right wall plate; a left screw and a right screw are arranged into internal thread holes of two catches on the front side surfaces of the support; and the tail ends of the left screw and the right screw respectively push against the inner side surfaces of the front left wall plate and the front right wall plate. The support is forced to move back and forth through adjusting the left screw and the right screw so as to control the included angle between the transmission roller and the film edge of a laser transfer film, so that holographic image-text information on the film surface can coincide with holographic image-text information on the second mother set.

column12: Silver nanometer material and application thereof
column13: The invention provides a silver nanometer material and application thereof. The silver nanometer material has a periodical structure formed by hexagonal silver nanometer particle arrays, and is suitable for preparing an ultra-fast optical switch with a near ultraviolet waveband of 350 to 450 nanometers. The silver nanometer material provided by the invention has a very high nonlinear refractive index in a resonance region of the silver; a switching speed of the near ultraviolet waveband ultra-fast optical switch prepared from the silver nanometer material can reach a sub-picosecond scale, and therefore the loss caused by the metal surface plasma resonance absorption is greatly reduced.

column12: Rubber-base flexible shielding material and preparation method thereof
column13: The invention provides a rubber-base flexible shielding material and a preparation method thereof. The shielding material uses radiation resistant styrene-butadiene rubber as a substrate. The substrate is improved in hardness and flexibility by an additive; original gum plastication and banburying (or opening milling) processes are used to uniformly spreading lead powder or boron carbide in the rubber substrate; and finally oxidization and crosslinking reaction are performed to form the radiation resistant rubber material having arbitrary plasticity, excellent shielding performance, excellent flexibility and excellent structural adaptability. The preparation process of the invention adopts a 'peroxidation' method rather than a 'vulcanization' method in the crosslinking reaction for forming the flexible shielding material, so the shielding material is free from sulfur and suitable for use in the field of nuclear power. Tests show that the shielding material has a lead weight content of 78 percent, a boron carbide weight content of more than 35 percent, a hardness of 43 DEG (Shore A) and a tensile elongation of 0.32mmPb and meets requirements of GB16363-1996 X Ray Protective Material Shielding Performance and Test Method in terms of other performance data.

column12: Sewage pressure pipeline supporting structure
column13: The sewage pressure pipeline supporting structure is characterized in that first vertical steel supporting columns are arranged on the two sides of a pipeline and correspond to the center of a box culvert respectively, and each first vertical steel supporting column is inserted into a weathered rock stratum; second vertical steel supporting columns are arranged on the two sides of the pipeline and correspond to the positions away from one end of the box culvert by a certain distance, and each second vertical steel supporting column is inserted into the weathered rock stratum. Third vertical steel supporting columns are arranged at the positions, away from the other end of the box culvert by a certain distance, of the two sides of the pipeline correspondingly, and each third vertical steel supporting column is inserted into the weathered rock stratum. First longitudinal steel supporting rods are welded among the first vertical steel supporting column, the second vertical steel supporting column and the third vertical steel supporting column and located on the top face of the pipeline, second longitudinal steel supporting rods are welded on the bottom face of the pipeline, and a transverse steel supporting rod is welded to the surface of each first longitudinal steel supporting rod. A third longitudinal steel supporting rod and a fourth longitudinal steel supporting rod are sequentially welded between the first vertical steel supporting column, the second vertical steel supporting column and the third vertical steel supporting column and located below the second longitudinal steel supporting rod.

column12: FREQUENCY-CONVERTED FREQUENCY-MODULATED SELF-INJECTION-LOCKED RADAR
column13: A FCFMSIL radar includes a SILO, a frequency conversion unit, an antenna unit, a demodulation unit and a processing unit. The frequency conversion unit converts an oscillation signal of the SILO into a FMCW signal. The antenna unit transmits the FMCW signal to an area as a transmitted signal and receives a reflected signal from the area as a received signal. The frequency conversion unit converts the received signal into an injection signal and injects it into the SILO. The demodulation unit demodulates the oscillation signal into an in-phase demodulated signal and a quadrature demodulated signal. The processing unit processes the in-phase and the quadrature demodulated signals to obtain a baseband signal and thus acquire a phase and a frequency of a tone in the frequency-domain baseband signal, and determines the tone corresponding to one or multiple objects based on the phase and frequency of the tone.

column12: Contact Resistance Reduction for Transistors

The method further includes depositing a metal layer extending into the contact opening. Horizontal portions, vertical portions, and corner portions of the metal layer have a substantially uniform thickness. An annealing process is performed to react the metal layer with the source/drain region to form a source/drain silicide region. The contact opening is filled to form a source/drain contact plug.

column12: METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR PERFORMING DE-BLOCKING FILTERING OF A VIDEO PICTURE
column13: Common video standards use de-blocking filtering for reducing blocking distortion between the different blocks or macroblocks of a picture. De-blocking filtering is done horizontally within a line and vertically over two lines, or four lines for MBAFF mode. A method for performing de-blocking filtering of a video picture comprises steps of reading data of a current line into an internal memory, performing horizontal filtering on the current line data, writing the horizontally filtered current line data to an external memory, reading data of a next line into the internal memory, reading horizontally filtered data of the current line from the external memory into the internal memory, performing vertical filtering on the horizontally filtered current line data and the next line data, and writing the vertically and horizontally filtered current line data to the external memory. The invention is especially advantageous for HD resolution processing.

column12: Fast manufacturing method of metal pipework product
column13: The invention is a fast manufacturing method of a metal pipework product. A fast molding procedure is conducted first by putting a mold prototype formed through manpower or machine in a flask. Then, by heating means, a sand mold is obtained by melting the mold prototype from the flask. Further, a molten liquid is poured into the sand mold. After the molten liquid is cooled and solidified, a forming mold is obtained. A pipework hydroforming procedure is conducted by putting a blank pipe in the forming mold which is then closed and a punch is placed into a punch placement channel formed between the corresponding faces of an upper mold and a lower mold. Subsequently, a liquid is injected into the interior of the blank pipe to be pressurized. Simultaneously, the punch is abutting to the end of the blank pipe. Therefore, the blank pipe which corresponds to the mold cavity is deformed to form a model pipework. The invention can manufacture metal pipework with complicated shape fast in low cost. and is suitable to manufacture metal pipework products in small amount and many variety.

column12: Single pass adaptive interpolation filter
column13: The invention provides a method for performing single-pass adaptive interpolation filtering, an encoder and a decoder, wherein the method for performing single-pass adaptive interpolation includes: receiving the video frames; selecting an interpolation filter from a competitive filter set; performing motion prediction on a current frame of the video frame utilizing the interpolation filter; encoding the current frame into the bitstream; and updating the competitive filter set for a next frame by using the optimal interpolation filter. The method for performing single-pass adaptive interpolation filtering and the encoder provided by the invention can reduce encoding delay and indirect expenditure of access of a memorizer. The encoder of the invention can improve the encoding efficiency.

column12: Differential pressure principle non-contact liquid level sensor
column13: The invention relates to the technical field of liquid level measurement, in particular to a differential pressure principle non-contact type liquid level sensor, the surface of an air chamber is fixedly connected with an air pipe, according to the principle that air pressure in a closed space is equal, different liquid levels are adopted for dividing the closed space into a plurality of closed spaces, and the liquid level detection function is achieved; the liquid level sensor not only can detect pure liquid with constant density, but also can detect non-pure liquid with uncertain density, such as a solid-liquid mixture, is particularly suitable for occasions with relatively high requirements on the relative detection precision of the liquid level in a mixed dirt discharge container, and well solves the problems that a contact type liquid level sensor is high in failure rate and low in detection precision. The liquid level sensor solves the problem that a conventional non-contact liquid level sensor cannot be installed due to a special use environment, is simple in structure and is not in contact with liquid to be detected, so that the production cost of the sensor is reduced, product faults caused by solid-liquid mixing are avoided, the product reliability is greatly improved, and the product quality is improved. And the use and maintenance cost of the product is greatly reduced.

column12: Apparatus for metal plating on a substrate
column13: An apparatus for metal plating on a substrate with through-holes includes a chamber that the substrate is fixed inside the chamber to be divided into two sections. column12: Vacuum linear machine importing device
column13: The present invention relates to a vacuum linear machine importing device, which comprises a base, which comprises two linear bearings arranged in the base and an inner bushing having a through hole and arranged between the two linear bearings, and a reciprocally movable shaft penetrated the base and extending through the two linear bearings and the through hole of the inner bushing. The shaft comprises a shaft body and the shaft body has an intermediate section on which a seat is formed. The seat receives a sealing ring fit thereto and in contact engagement with the inner bushing. The shaft body has an outer diameter that is smaller than an inner diameter of the through hole of the inner bushing in order to reduce the contact area between the inner bushing and the shaft. And, the inner bushing is coated with a diamond-like carbon film to lower down frictional coefficient and reduce frictional force so as to effectively reduce wear and abrasion.

column12: Method for source/drain contact formation in semiconductor devices using common doping and common etching to n-type and p-type source/drains
column13: A method includes providing a structure that includes a substrate, a first gate structure and a second gate structure over the substrate, and a first source/drain (S/D) feature and a second S/D feature over the substrate. The first S/D feature is adjacent to the first gate structure, the second S/D feature is adjacent to the second gate structure, the first S/D feature is configured for an n-type transistor, and the second S/D feature is configured for a p-type transistor. The method further includes introducing a p-type dopant into both the first and the second S/D features. After the introducing of the p-type dopant, the method further includes performing an etching process to the first and the second S/D features, wherein the etching process etches the first S/D feature faster than it etches the second S/D feature.

column12: / METHOD FOR SOURCE/DRAIN CONTACT FORMATION IN SEMICONDUCTOR DEVICES
column13: A method comprises a step of providing a structure, wherein the structure comprises: a substrate; first and second gate structures on the substrate; first and second source/drain (S/D) features on the substrate; a first dielectric layer on sidewalls of the first and second gate structures and on the first and second S/D features; and a second dielectric layer on the first dielectric layer. The first and second S/D features are adjacent to the first and second gate structures, respectively. The first and second S/D features include different materials. The method further comprises the steps of: etching the first and second dielectric layers to expose the first and second S/D features; doping the first and second S/D features with a p-type dopant; and after doping the p-type dopant, performing a selective etching process for the first and second S/D features. The selective etching process recesses the first S/D feature faster than recessing of the second S/D feature.

column12: Stencil design for solder paste printing
column13: A stencil design for solder paste printing, or other metal stencil printing, is disclosed. A stencil for stencil printing of solder onto a semiconductor wafer for semiconductor wafer bumping includes a substrate. The substrate has a hole defined therein substantially shaped to correspond to and receptive to the semiconductor wafer. An interior edge of the substrate surrounds the hole, and has an upper lip under which the semiconductor wafer is positioned. The upper lip of the interior edge of the substrate surrounding the hole substantially prevents the solder from flowing onto sides and a bottom of the semiconductor wafer during stencil printing of the solder. The cross-profile shape of the upper lip may in one embodiment be rectangular, whereas in another embodiment be triangular.

column12: Method for Source/Drain Contact Formation in Semiconductor Devices
column13: A method includes providing a structure that includes a substrate; first and second gate structures over the substrate; first and second source/drain (S/D) features over the substrate; a first dielectric layer over sidewalls of the first and second gate structures and the first and second S/D features; and a second dielectric layer over the first dielectric layer. The first and second S/D features are adjacent to the first and second gate structures respectively. The first and second S/D features comprise different materials. The method further includes etching the first and second dielectric layers to expose the first and second S/D features; doping a p-type dopant to the first and second S/D features; and performing a selective etching process to the first and second S/D features after the doping of the p-type dopant. The selective etching process recesses the first S/D feature faster than it recesses the second S/D feature.

column13: A Ferris wheel-like stripping or cleaning mechanism that can be used in semiconductor fabrication, such as in photoresist or other stripping, or wafer or other cleaning, is disclosed. column13: Ein Verfahren umfasst das Bereitstellen einer Struktur umfassend ein Substrat; eine erste Gatestruktur und eine zweite Gatestruktur über dem Substrat; ein erstes Source/Drain-(S/D) -Merkmal und ein zweites S/D-Merkmal über dem Substrat; eine erste dielektrische Schicht über Seitenwänden der ersten und der zweiten Gatestruktur und über dem ersten und dem zweiten S/D-Merkmal; und eine zweite dielektrische Schicht über der ersten dielektrischen Schicht. column12: Method to improve reliability for flip-chip device for limiting pad design
column13: A method of fabricating a solder bump including the following steps. A UBM over a substrate.having an exposed pad portion is provided. The UBM being in electrical contact with the pad portion. A first patterning layer is formed over the UBM. The first patterning layer including a photosensitive material sensitive to light having a first wavelength. A second patterning layer is formed over the first patterning layer. The second patterning layer including a photosensitive material sensitive to light having a second wavelength. The first patterning layer is selectively exposed with the light having the first wavelength, leaving a first unexposed portion substantially centered over the pad portion between first exposed portions. The second patterning layer is selectively exposed with the light having the second wavelength, leaving a second unexposed portion wider than, and substantially centered over, the first unexposed portion of the exposed first patterning layer. The second unexposed portion of the exposed second patterning layer being between exposed portions. The second unexposed portion of the exposed second patterning layer and the first unexposed portion of the exposed first patterning layer are removed to form opening. A solder plug is formed within the opening. The exposed portions of the exposed first patterning layer and the exposed portions of the exposed second patterning layer are removed. The solder plug is reflowed to form a solder bump.

column12: Fabricated highway steel bridge end post
column13: The utility model relates to a fabricated highway steel bridge end post. The end column is easy and convenient to machine and manufacture, the erecting and assembling speed is high, nonlinear deformation of the structure can be reduced, and the design defects of an existing assembly type road steel bridge are effectively overcome. The main body chord member adopts double channel steels, the channel steels are arranged in a back-to-back manner, the back parts of the channel steels are welded with the supporting plates and the connecting plates to form an integral framework, the joint plates adopt a porous type and are welded at the ends of the channel steel framework, the joint plates are welded with the cross beam base plates, the end columns are connected with the upper chord member and the lower chord member of the truss sheet through the steel pins, and the end columns are connected with the support through the steel pins. And finally, the whole is formed and is jointly stressed. The end columns are symmetrical in structure and can be quickly assembled and connected with the truss, deflection influence caused by nonlinearity of the structure can be reduced, and technical support is provided for quick assembly design of a novel assembly type road steel bridge.

column12: Precious metal hydrogenation catalyst, preparation method and application thereof
column13: The invention discloses a preparation method of a precious metal hydrogenation catalyst. The preparation method comprises the following steps: (1) roasting the original clay soil at high temperature, then enabling the roasted original clay soil to react with mixed acid, and pulping to prepare slurry, wherein the mixed acid is a mixture of strong acid and weak acid; (2) adding a Y type molecular sieve to the slurry in the step, stirring uniformly, adding an aluminum-containing acid solution and an alkaline solution under a parallel flow condition, carrying out a gel forming reaction, and after gel forming, carrying out ageing, filtering, washing and drying to obtain silicon-containing alumina powder; (3) adding an adhesion agent to the silicon-containing alumina powder prepared in the step (2), and carrying out extrusion molding, drying and baking to obtain a silicon-containing alumina supporter; (4) preparing a noble metal aqueous solution containing esters and organic acid, adding the supporter prepared in the step (3) to the solution to be impregnated, and after impregnation, drying and roasting to obtain the precious metal hydrogenation catalyst. The catalyst has the advantages of small active component crystal grain, low dispersity, low strong acid center and the like; the catalyst can be used for paraffin hydrogenation production to produce a food-grade paraffin product.

column12: Alarm threshold value adaptive method for distributed optical fiber temperature sensor
column13: The invention relates to an alarm threshold value adaptive method for a distributed optical fiber temperature sensor, and belongs to the technical field of optical fiber sensing. The method includes: utilizing a DTS (digital transmission system) mainframe to control a light source to send out periodic light pulse to enter a sensing optical fiber, collecting Stokes signals and anti-Stokes signals of backward Raman scattering, calculating temperature distribution of the sensing optical fiber according to temperature of a reference optical fiber ring inside the mainframe, and calculating an alarm threshold value according to ambient temperature curve function. The alarm threshold value is automatically adjusted according to temperature of external environment, so that problems of false alarm and alarm failure of conventional single threshold value are solved, system adaptability is improved, and system reliability is improved.

column12: Airspace operation risk assessment method based on fuzzy matter element analysis
column13: The invention provides an airspace operation risk assessment method based on fuzzy matter element analysis, and the method comprises the steps: summarizing an airspace operation risk index into a conflict risk index and an operation situation risk index, and building a comprehensive operation risk assessment index system; calculating the weight of each evaluation index by adopting an objective weighting method; analyzing a classic domain and a node domain of the airspace operation risk matter-element model by adopting a clustering algorithm; the risk level of an evaluation object is judged in combination with the fuzzy mathematics theory, a membership function is adopted as the objective measurement of fuzziness, and a membership degree calculation method is given; and finally, according to the index weight obtained in the above steps and the membership degree of the evaluation object about each risk level, completing airspace operation risk level determination by taking the maximum membership degree as a principle. According to the method, intervention of human subjective factors on operation risk level judgment is avoided, and since parameters such as an evaluation system and the total number of risk levels can be flexibly set, practicability and expansibility of an algorithm are ensured, and a basis can be provided for risk airspace identification.

column12: Flight flow generation method based on probability distribution characteristics
column13: The invention provides a flight flow generation method based on probability distribution characteristics, which comprises the following steps: taking Poisson distribution followed by a current actualtakeoff flight flow as an example, calculating the number of takeoff flights in unit time, giving corresponding elements to the takeoff flights in the unit time by comprehensively considering the distribution characteristics of a takeoff interval, a target airport and a model, generating a take-off flight flow of a single airport; generating a landing flight flow: generating the maximum landing flight flow of the single airport according to the distribution characteristics of the wake flow interval and the landing flight runway occupation interval; and generating a mixed flight flow: based onthe take-off flow and the landing flow, considering the capacity constraint and the take-off and landing interval constraint in actual operation, and generating the hybrid flight flow by taking departure priority as a principle. The method depends on the probability distribution characteristics, fully considers the objectivity of actual operation, can flexibly and diverse generate the required flight flow, and provides reliable data support for operation decision, simulation deduction and other subdivision business fields in the air traffic control field.

column12: Macroporous alumina and preparation method thereof
column13: The invention discloses a preparation method of a macroporous alumina carrier. The method comprises the following steps: (1) preparing a solution containing grease and organic acid, an acidic aluminum solution and a basic aluminate solution, and respectively marking into a solution A, a solution B and a solution C; (2) combining the solution B and the solution C to perform gelation reaction, regulating pH to be 9.0 to 11.0, wherein the pH is preferably is 9.5 to 10.5; controlling the reaction temperature to be 60 to 95 DEG C, wherein the reaction temperature is preferably 75 to 85 DEG C; performing ageing, filtering, washing and drying after the gelation reaction, wherein the solution A is added before or during gelation; the solution A, the solution B and the solution C are preferably combined to perform the gelation reaction; (3) forming the material obtained in step (2), and then drying and roasting to obtain the macroporous alumina carrier, The macroporous alumina carrier prepared by the method has the advantages of being large in aperture, large in pore volume and high in strength.

column12: Laser micro-texturing self-lubricating treatment method for friction pairs
column13: The invention discloses a laser micro-texturing self-lubricating treatment method for friction pairs, which relates to a friction pair self-lubricating technology. According to the invention, the surface of a friction pair is subjected to laser micro-texturing treatment, the diameter of a micro pit is 45-130 microns, the depth of the micro pit is 10-80 microns, the area-occupied rate of the micro pit is 20-38%, the distance between the micro pits is 110-300 microns, and a self-lubricating composite material is embedded in the surface of the friction pair by using a secondary thermal pressurizing method, so that the surface friction coefficient of the obtained friction pair is low, thereby reducing friction and abrasion and improving the antifriction and wear-resistance combination properties of the friction pair.

column12: Hydrogenation catalyst as well as preparation method and application thereof
column13: The invention discloses a preparation method of a hydrogenation refining catalyst. The method comprises the following steps: (1) performing high-temperature calcination on original clay, enabling the calcinated clay to react with mixed acid, and pulping so as to form a serous fluid, wherein the mixed acid is the mixture of strong acid and weak acid; (2) adding a Y-shaped molecular sieve into the serous fluid obtained in the step (1), uniformly stirring, adding an acid solution containing aluminum and an alkaline solution in a concurrent flow manner to carry out a gelatinizing reaction, and aging, filtering, washing and drying, so as to obtain alumina powder containing silicon; (3) adding an adhesive into the alumina powder containing silicon, which is prepared in the step (2), and performing extrusion molding, drying and calcination, so as to obtain an alumina carrier containing silicon; (4) preparing a nickel-tungsten active-component solution which contains grease and an organic acid, adding the carrier prepared in the step (3) into the nickel-tungsten active-component solution to dip, and drying and calcinating, so as to obtain the hydrogenation catalyst. Appropriate bonding force is generated between the catalyst carrier and active components, and the degree of dispersion of the active components is moderate. The catalyst is applied in a paraffin hydrorefining reaction, and has the advantages of high stability, high quality of paraffin hydrorefining products, and the like.

column13: The invention discloses a preparation method of a nickel-based catalyst, which comprises the following steps that (1) pseudo-boehmite powder is added to an acid solution to form alumina collosol; (2) a nickel salt solution containing polyhydroxyaldehyde and organic acid is prepared; and (3) an alkaline precipitant solution is prepared; the alkaline precipitant solution and the nickel salt solution in Step (2) are merged and added to the alumina collosol prepared in Step (1) for a precipitation reaction; and the finished catalyst is obtained by ageing, washing, drying and roasting after reaction completion. The catalyst prepared by the method is high in active ingredient nickel dispersity and small in grain size; an interaction force of the catalyst and a carrier is moderate; and the catalyst can be used in the fields of petroleum processing, chemical engineering, environmental protection and the like, and is particularly suitable for a paraffin secondary hydrofining catalyst.

column12: EPITAKTISCHE SOURCE/DRAIN-STRUKTUREN FÜRMULTIGATE-VORRICHTUNGEN UND DEREN HERSTELLUNGSVERFAHREN
column13: Hierin offenbart sind epitaktische Source/Drain-Strukturen zum Verbessern der Leistung von Multigate-Vorrichtungen, wie etwa Finnen-Feldeffekttransistoren (FinFETs) oder Gate-all-around-Feldeffekttransistoren (GAA-FETs), und Verfahren zum Herstellen der epitaktischen Source/Drain-Strukturen. Eine beispielhafte Vorrichtung weist ein dielektrisches Substrat auf. Die Vorrichtung weist weiterhin Folgendes auf: eine Kanalschicht; ein Gate, das über der Kanalschicht angeordnet ist; und eine epitaktische Source/Drain-Struktur, die benachbart zu der Kanalschicht angeordnet ist. Die Kanalschicht, das Gate und die epitaktische Source/Drain-Struktur sind über dem dielektrischen Substrat angeordnet. Die epitaktische Source/Drain-Struktur weist einen inneren Teil mit einer ersten Dotierungskonzentration und einen äußeren Teil mit einer zweiten Dotierungskonzentration auf, die niedriger als die erste Dotierungskonzentration ist. Der innere Teil kontaktiert physisch das dielektrische Substrat, und der äußere Teil ist zwischen dem inneren Teil und der Kanalschicht angeordnet. Bei einigen Ausführungsformen kontaktiert der äußere Teil physisch das dielektrische Substrat.

column12: In-situ aerobic cometabolism of chlorinated hydrocarbons using toluene vapor as the primary substrate
column13: An in-situ aerobic cometabolic method for delivering toluene vapor as the primary substrate to aquifer contaminated by chlorinated hydrocarbons (e.g., trichloroethylene). While the prior art neat toluene instead of toluene vapor was injected, excessive microbial growth and clogging occurred near the well screens. Delivery of toluene in vapor state provides effective mixing with microorganisms and the contaminants in the aquifer. Furthermore, by delivering toluene in vapor state avoids potential clogging near the injection points due to excessive microbial growth.

column12: / EPITAXIAL SOURCE/DRAIN STRUCTURES FOR MULTIGATE DEVICES AND METHODS OF FABRICATING THEREOF
column13: Disclosed are an epitaxial source/drain structure for enhancing performance of a multigate device, such as fin-like field-effect transistors (FETs) or gate-all-around (GAA) FETs, and a method of producing the epitaxial source/drain structure. An exemplary device includes a dielectric substrate. The device further includes a channel layer, a gate disposed over the channel layer, and an epitaxial source/drain structure disposed adjacent to the channel layer. The channel layer, the gate, and the epitaxial source/drain structure are disposed over the dielectric substrate. The epitaxial source/drain structure includes an inner portion having a first dopant concentration and an outer portion having a second dopant concentration that is less than the first dopant concentration. The inner portion physically comes in contact with the dielectric substrate, and the outer portion is disposed between the inner portion and the channel layer. In some embodiments, the outer portion physically comes in contact with the dielectric substrate.

column12: Semiconductor structures and methods for fabricating the same
column13: Semiconductor structures and methods are provided. An exemplary method according to the present disclosure includes forming a first source/drain feature, a second source/drain feature and an interlayer dielectric (ILD) layer over the first and second source/drain features. The method also includes removing a portion of the ILD layer to form a cut feature opening and forming a hybrid cut feature therein to divide a to-be-formed metal layer into multiple pieces as source/drain contacts. The hybrid cut feature includes a conformal dielectric liner over the cut feature opening and a dielectric filler over the dielectric liner. During the formation of a source/drain contact opening, at least a portion of the dielectric liner extending along a sidewall of the dielectric filler is partially and selectively removed, leading to a dimension-reduced hybrid cut feature and thus a reduced spacing between two adjacent source/drain contacts.

column12: Method of forming backside power rails

In an embodiment, an exemplary method of forming the semiconductor structure includes forming a fin structure extending from a front side of a substrate, recessing a source region of the fin structure to form a source opening, forming a semiconductor plug under the source opening, planarizing the substrate to expose the semiconductor plug from a back side of the substrate, performing a pre-amorphous implantation (PAI) process to amorphize the substrate, replacing the amorphized substrate with a dielectric layer, and replacing the semiconductor plug with a backside source contact. By performing the PAI process, crystalline semiconductor is amorphized and may be substantially removed. column12: Flush system for dry film photoresist remover
column13: A flush system comprising a network of conduits, valves and screens that can be interposed between the process container and solvent re-claim tank components of a dry film photoresist (DFR) remover system, for example, that is used in the processing and packaging of integrated circuit chips. By operation of the valves in the flush system, DFR particles can be removed from the DFR remover system in order to prevent or minimize particle clogging of a particle filter in the DFR remover system. The screens in the flush system can be periodically cleaned by reverse flow of solvent or by operation of a nitrogen and DI (deionized) water purge system.

column13: The invention provides a signal processing device, a signal processing method and a corresponding electronic device. The signal processing apparatus includes a signal transmission port, a first signal processing circuit, a second signal processing circuit, and a control circuit. The signal transmission port is shared between a first signal processing operation and a second signal processing operation. The first signal processing circuit performs the first signal processing operation, wherein when the signal processing apparatus operates, the first signal processing circuit is not required to be consistently enabled to use the signal transmission port for signal transmission. The signal processing device, the signal processing method and the corresponding electronic device could reduce the number of the pins so as to decrease the chip area and the product cost.

column12: Novel method to improve bump reliability for flip chip device
column13: A new method is provided for the creation of a solder bump. Conventional methods are initially followed, creating a patterned layer of Under Bump Metal over the surface of a contact pad. A layer of photoresist is next deposited, this layer of photoresist is patterned and developed creating a resist mask having a T-shape opening aligned with the contact pad. This T-shaped opening is filled with a solder compound, creating a T-shaped layer of solder compound on the surface of the layer of UBM. The layer of photoresist is removed, exposing the created T-shaped layer of solder compound, further exposing the layer of UBM. The layer of UBM is etched using the T-shaped layer of solder compound as a mask. Reflow of the solder compound results in creating a solder ball.

column12: Method for improving bump reliability for flip chip devices
column13: A new method is provided for the creation of a solder bump. Conventional methods are initially followed, creating a patterned layer of Under Bump Metal over the surface of a contact pad. A layer of photoresist is next deposited, this layer of photoresist is patterned and developed creating a resist mask having a T-shape opening aligned with the contact pad. This T-shaped opening is filled with a solder compound, creating a T-shaped layer of solder compound on the surface of the layer of UBM. The layer of photoresist is removed, exposing the Created T-shaped layer of solder compound, further exposing the layer of UBM. The layer of UBM is etched using the T-shaped layer of solder compound as a mask. Reflow of the solder compound results in creating a solder ball.

column12: Portable ultrasonic, infrared and ultraviolet detector based on image synthesis technology
column13: The invention relates to a portable ultrasonic, infrared and ultraviolet detector based on the image synthesis technology. The detector comprises an ultrasonic wave visible module, an infrared detection module, an ultraviolet detection module, a control display module and a power source. The ultrasonic wave visible module is used for synchronously collecting and synthesizing ultrasonic array signals and visible light images to obtain an ultrasonic visible light image. The infrared detection module is used for synchronously collecting infrared images with the ultrasonic wave visible module. The ultraviolet detection module is used for synchronously collecting ultraviolet images with the ultrasonic wave visible module. The control display module is connected with the ultrasonic wave visible module, and the infrared detection module and the ultraviolet detection module are used for synthesizing and displaying the obtained ultrasonic visible light images, infrared images and ultraviolet images. The power source is used for supplying power to the ultrasonic wave visible module, the infrared detection module, the ultraviolet detection module and the control display module. Compared with the prior art, the portable ultrasonic, infrared and ultraviolet detector has the advantages of being high in detection precision, convenient to use and the like.

column12: Monitor for intra-operative transesophageal multi-modal monitoring and signal collecting and processing method based on monitor
column13: The invention provides a monitor for intra-operative transesophageal multi-modal monitoring. The monitor comprises a host, a holding shell, a flexible hose, an electrocardio-electrode, a body temperature probe, an oxyhemoglobin saturation probe, an ultrasonic transducer, a transmission mechanism and a measuring grating; the holding shell is used for operating holding; the flexible hose is connected with the holding shell through a pipe joint; the electrocardio-electrode is embedded into the portion, corresponding to a monitored part, of the hose wall of the flexible hose and used for collecting electrocardiosignals; the body temperature probe is embedded into the portion, corresponding to the monitored part, of the hose wall of the flexible hose and used for collecting human body center temperature signals; the oxyhemoglobin saturation probe is embedded into the portion, corresponding to the monitored part, of the hose wall of the flexible hose and used for collecting oxyhemoglobin saturation signals; the ultrasonic transducer is installed at the tail end of the flexible hose through a hinge shaft; the transmission mechanism is installed in the holding shell and used for driving the ultrasonic transducer to swing; the measuring grating is use for measuring the transmission displacement of the transmission mechanism; the electrocardio-electrode, the oxyhemoglobin saturation probe, the body temperature probe, the ultrasonic transducer and the measuring grating are all in signal connection with the host through signal lines separately; the transmission mechanism is composed of a chain wheel, a chain matched with the chain wheel and two metal wires located in the flexible hose. The monitor integrates an ultrasonic cardiogram signal, an electrocardiogram signal, an oxyhemoglobin saturation signal, a human body center temperature signal and the like.

column12: Intelligent power grid accident identification method based on rule learning
column13: The invention provides a power grid accident intelligent identification method based on rule learning, and the method comprises the steps: obtaining a fault type, obtaining a fault type combination when a power grid has an accident and does not have an accident in a period of time according to historical data, and obtaining a rule training data set X according to the fault type combination; obtaining an empirical measurement information amount S (X) according to the rule training data set X; acquiring an information gain z (X, x) of the fault type x to the rule training data set X according tothe empirical measurement information amount S (X); taking the fault category with the maximum information gain z (X, x) as a first main rule feature, obtaining the information gain of other fault categories for the first main rule feature, and repeating the above process to obtain a rule decision tree; inputting the to-be-identified power grid operation data into the rule decision tree, whereinthe rule decision tree outputs the power grid accident identification result, so that the fault identification processing speed can be reduced, the real-time monitoring of the power grid system can berealized, and the normal transmission of electric energy is ensured.
