column12: Security encryption method for cloud computing based matrix multiplication outsourcing process
column13: The invention discloses a security encryption method for cloud computing based matrix multiplication outsourcing process to solve the technical problem of overcoming the shortage of disclosing data privacy in the existing technology, and better protect the input data privacy of matrix multiplication. The security encryption method is completed by improved matrix multiplication outsourcing software, and mainly comprises improving a secret key module, an encryption module and a decryption module; the secret key module generates a secret key according to the matrix size, and the secret key is composed of 4k random vectors; then, the encryption module adds matrix Z1 and Z2 generated by the secret key to input matrixes X and Y respectively, and encrypts each element in the matrixes X and Y; a calculation module calculates encrypted matrix multiplication problems; a verification module verifies calculation results; the decryption module decrypts final calculation results according to the secret key. The security encryption method can encrypt each element in the matrixes X and Y during encryption, protects the privacy of each element including the number of zero elements, and better protects the privacy of input data.

column12: Drag-cup type microwave-induced modified emulsified asphalt thick slurry, and construction method and device thereof
column13: The invention relates to a drag-cup type microwave-induced modified emulsified asphalt thick slurry, and a construction method and a device thereof. According to the invention, base asphalt, a ferric oxide modified polyester resin latex, a modified latex, a warm mixing agent, an emulsifier and water are utilized to prepare drag-cup type microwave-induced modified emulsified asphalt which is mixed with an aggregate, mineral powder, fiber and water for pavement partial repair by adopting a vehicle-mounted thick repairing vehicle, wherein concrete steps comprise traffic closing, original pavement cleaning, setting-out, construction equipment debugging in place, mixing, synchronous auxiliary heating with a microwave heating box, paving, rolling compaction, initial maintenance and quality inspection, and traffic opening. The drag-cup type microwave-induced modified emulsified asphalt provided by the invention has pavement performance no lower than the pavement performance of ordinary modified emulsified asphalt; meanwhile, the performances of cold mixed thick slurry can rapidly meet the performance requirements of hot mixed asphalt thick slurry in site through the sensitivity of vehicle-mounted microwave-induced modified emulsified asphalt to microwave.

column12: Penetration method for mined metro station and running tunnel in delta-shaped junction
column13: The invention discloses a penetration method for a mined metro station and a running tunnel in a delta-shaped junction mode. The penetration method for the mined metro station and the running tunnel in a delta-shaped junction mode comprises the steps that when excavation is constructed to the junction of a transverse channel and a station main tunnel, lower bench soil bass of the transverse channel is retained; the retained lower bench soil bass of the transverse channel is used as a working surface, an exhaust tunnel is excavated and exhaust tunnel preliminary support is constructed timely; after the exhaust tunnel is penetrated, expanding excavation of the station main tunnel is carried out, and station main tunnel preliminary support and temporary support are carried out timely; residual soil mass of the transverse channel is excavated and constructed, and transverse channel preliminary support and transverse channel secondary support are constructed timely; and the running tunnel is excavated from the constructed transverse channel, the residual soil mass of the transverse channel is excavated, and the station main tunnel preliminary support and the station main tunnel secondary support are constructed timely. The exhaust tunnel is excavated by using the constructed transverse channel upper bench, then excavation of the running tunnel is carried out after the lower bench isexcavated, the penetration surface is reinforced, and the convenience brought by a bench cut method is fully utilized.

column12: Radar radio frequency front-end active ring transmit-receive system
column13: The invention discloses a radar radio frequency front-end active annular receiving and transmitting system, which comprises two doubly-fed circularly polarized antennas, an annular coupler, two low noise amplifiers and a Wilkinson power divider. A signal to be transmitted is divided into two paths of signals with the same amplitude and opposite phases through the annular coupler, then two paths ofsignals feed the two double-fed antennas and are transmitted respectively, and the signals received by the two antennas pass through the two low-noise amplifiers respectively and then are synthesizedand output by the Wilkinson power divider. The system is simple in structure, low in cost and high in reliability, one-way annular transmission of signals can be easily achieved, the isolation degreeof a signal input port and a signal output port is improved, and meanwhile the problems of leakage cancellation and partial coupling can be solved when the system serves as a single-antenna system.

column12: Direct-current double-power-source-paralleled switching device
column13: The invention relates to a direct-current double-power-source-paralleled switching device which comprises a diode D1, a diode D2, a diode D3, a diode D4, a voltmeter V1, a voltmeter V2, a direct-current air switch QK1and a direct-current air switch QK2. The diode D1, the direct-current air switch QK1 and the diode D3 are sequentially in series connection to form a direct-current system 1, the voltmeter V1 and the direct-current air switch QK1 are in parallel connection, the diode D2, the direct-current air switch QK2 and the diode D4 are sequentially in series connection to form a direct-current system 2, the voltmeter V2 and the direct-current air switch QK2 are in parallel connection, and the direct-current system 1 and the direct-current system 2 are parallelly connected to be connected with an photoelectric conversion device. The direct-current double-power-source-paralleled switching device has the advantages that when a first power source is in failure or outage, and the other power source is switched on by the device, so that uninterrupted power source input is realized, continuous running of equipment can be realized, and safety and reliability of a power grid are improved.

column12: An apparatus for switching double DC power supplies in parallel
column13: The utility model relates to an apparatus for switching double DC power supplies in parallel. The apparatus comprises a diode D1, a diode D2, a diode D3, a diode D4, a voltmeter V1, a voltmeter V2, a DC air switch QK1, and a DC air switch QK2. The diode D1, the DC air switch QK1, and the diode D3 are successively connected in series in order to form a DC system 1. The voltmeter V1 is connected with the DC air switch QK1 in parallel. The diode D2, the DC air switch QK2, and the diode D4 are successively connected in series in order to form a DC system 2. The voltmeter V2 is connected with the DC air switch QK2 in parallel. The DC system 1 and the DC system 2 are connected in parallel and then are connected with a photoelectric conversion device. column12: Large square billet continuous casting machine crystallizer molten steel liquid level calibration scale device
column13: The utility model discloses a large square billet continuous casting machine crystallizer molten steel liquid level calibration scale device which belongs to the technical field of continuous castingequipment and is used for improving the detection accuracy of the crystallizer molten steel liquid level. column13: The invention provides a system using cloud manage and green energy technology for fish ponds. A control device is connected to the at least one sensor, the camera, and the at least one peripheral device to receive a sensing signal, and a captured image signal. column12: Airport scene real-time state adaptive adjustment-based flight push-out control method
column13: The invention discloses a flight push-out control method based on airport scene real-time state adaptive adjustment. The method comprises the following steps: firstly, analyzing a departure process of a flight, adopting a classical N-control mode as a basic strategy for departure flight push-out control, and carrying out adaptive adjustment on a push-out control threshold according to a real-time state of an airport scene; if the number of flights waiting to be pushed out at the current gate position is large, the push-out control threshold value is properly increased to increase the push-out number, so that more flights are promoted to be pushed out as soon as possible, and gate position resources are released; and if the number of the flights waiting in line on the current taxiway is large, the push-out control threshold value is properly reduced to reduce the push-out number, so that taxiway congestion is relieved, and fuel consumption is reduced. By adopting the method, the flight departure process can be maintained in a relatively stable state, the dependence on artificial experience is avoided, a more intelligent push-out control scheme is automatically provided, and the total cost of flight departure is effectively reduced.

column12: Method for controlling cracks of Q235 round steel under high pulling speed condition
column13: The invention relates to the field of round steel rolling, in particular to a method for controlling cracks of Q235 round steel under the condition of high pulling speed, the Q235 round steel comprises the following chemical components in percentage by weight: 0.13-0.17% of C, 0.10-0.15% of Si, 0.40-0.70% of Mn, 0.015% < P < = 0.022%, 0.01% < S < = 0.015%, 0.11% < Cr < = 0.30%, 0.10% < Ni < = 0.50%, 0.05% < Cu < = 0.40%, and less than 0.006% of N, Mn/S is controlled to be greater than 15, Mn/Si is controlled to be greater than 2.5, and the balance of Fe. By controlling the weight percentage content of the specific chemical components of the molten steel before converter smelting and the molten steel at the end point of the converter, the Q235 round steel with the chemical components and the weight percentage thereof meeting the requirements is obtained without performing deep deoxidation on the molten steel through LF refining, VD vacuum treatment and the like in a traditional process, the smelting cost is reduced, and meanwhile the production efficiency is improved. And when the Q235 round steel is rolled under the subsequent high-pulling-speed condition, the generation of cracks and the sizes of the cracks can be effectively reduced.

column12: Driving motor system sound quality objective evaluation feature extraction method
column13: The invention provides a driving motor system sound quality objective evaluation feature extraction method, which comprises the following steps of S1, establishing a driving motor system sound sample database, and obtaining a subjective evaluation result; s2, based on the sound sample in the step S1, combining the characteristics of the sound sample of the driving motor, preliminarily selecting objective parameters of the driving motor system, calculating objective parameter values, and constructing an objective parameter data set X of the driving motor system; and S3, based on the objective parameter data set X constructed in the step S2, objective parameters with relatively high correlation are eliminated by adopting a condensation type hierarchical clustering analysis method, and a screened objective parameter data set Y of the driving motor system is formed. The beneficial effects of the invention are that the method achieves the dimension simplification of an objective evaluation model, reduces the complexity of a sound quality prediction model, and lays a foundation for the sound quality evaluation of a driving motor system for a new energy vehicle.

column12: Application of impressed-current cathodic protection to prevent metal corrosion and oxidation
column13: A new method is provided for the processing of metals, most notably copper, such that damage to exposed surfaces of these metals is prevented. During a step of semiconductor processing, which results in exposing a metal surface to a wet substance having a pH value, a voltage is applied to the metal that is exposed. The value of the applied voltage can, dependent on the value of the pH constant of the wet substance, be selected such that the exposed metal surface is protected against alkaline effects of the wet substance.

column12: Beverage packing box with tearing port
column13: The utility model relates to a beverage packing box with a tearing opening, in particular relates to the beverage packing box with an unsealed structure. In order to solve the problem that the notches for the tearing opening of the prior packing box are positioned at the bottom part of the adhesion edge, which is inconvenient for pouring the drink. The utility model provides the beverage packing box with a tearing opening. A box body is in the shape of quadrangular prism and comprises a top part of the box and a bottom part of the box, wherein, both ends of the adhesion edge of the top part of the box extend out of the box body, and the extending part is the vertex angle plane. The adhesion edges are in abutting joint and are bonded with each other, and the two vertex angle planes are folded towards the adjacent side face and tightly pressed on the side face. The adhesion edge of one of the vertex angle plane is provided with a tearing opening line, and the notches of the tearing opening line extend towards the vertex angle plane and are symmetrically distributed on both sides of the adhesion edge of the vertex angle plane. A closed tearing opening line is formed on the vertex angle. While being used, the vertex angle plane sticking to the side face of the box is turned upwards and pulled apart, and the adhesive strip is torn downwards to form an outlet for the beverage, so that the beverage can be easily poured out.

column12: Electric pincer brake
column13: The invention discloses an electric pincer brake. The electric pincer brake comprises a hanging beam, an upper pincer body, a lower pincer body, a friction sheet, an installation seat, a return spring, a spiral lifter, a disc spring press rod, a lever and a connecting rod. The friction sheet is positioned between the upper pincer body and the lower pincer body. The hanging beam is positioned in the middle of the electric pincer brake; and the two ends of the hanging beam are fixed at the top end of a vertical shaft respectively. The return spring is sleeved on the vertical shaft. One side of the hanging beam is provided with the spiral lifter; one end of the disc spring press rod positioned on the lever in the middle of the upper pincer body is hinged with the upper pincer body; the other end of the lever is hinged with one end of the connecting rod; the other end of the connecting rod is hinged with a screw rod; and the connecting rod is arranged on the upper surface of the upper pincer body through a connection ear sheet on the surface of the upper pincer body. The wearing capacity of the friction sheet can be automatically compensated, so that the electric pincer brake has the characteristics of low energy consumption, small volume, and convenience in use, and is suitable for braking of large-scale machinery.

column12: Bridge support padstone and preformed hole integrated construction mold
column13: A bridge support padstone and preformed hole integrated construction mold comprises a plurality of side molds and a positioning frame. The side molds are connected end to end to form a cuboid structure, the bottom and the top end of the cuboid structure are open, transverse open grooves are formed in the tops of the transversely-arranged side molds, the transverse open grooves are formed in the length directions of the side molds, and the positioning frame is installed on the side molds through the transverse open grooves. According to the utility model, the plane position of the preformed hole can be quickly and accurately positioned and fixed, and the deviation of the preformed hole caused by subsequent construction is avoided; the preformed hole die is a steel die, is high in strength and rigidity, is not prone to deformation or damage, and can be recycled and used repeatedly. The step surface of the preformed hole mold can provide reference for plastering of the top surface of the padstone, the elevation and flatness of the top surface of the padstone are accurately controlled, and the construction quality of the padstone is effectively improved.

column12: Alliance chain consensus method introducing supervision mechanism, blockchain network and storage medium
column13: The invention relates to the technical field of block chains, and particularly discloses an alliance chain consensus method introducing a supervision mechanism, a block chain network and a storage medium. The method includes: running an alliance chain network through a creation node, wherein the alliance chain network comprises a supervision account and alliance chain member accounts, and the decision right of the supervision account is greater than the sum of the decision rights of the alliance chain member accounts; activating a block output node of the alliance chain member account by obtaining votes of the supervision account; when the number of the activated block output nodes reaches a preset number, transferring the block output right of the alliance chain member node to the block output nodes controlled by the alliance chain member node respectively, and enabling each activated block output node to execute the block output right according to a preset rule. The problems of resource waste and low transaction throughput of a block chain system can be solved, the problems of difficult governance of an existing public chain and the like can also be avoided, meanwhile, the flexibility of actual operation is considered, and the method has very high application value and economic benefits.

column12: Laser output device
column13: The invention discloses a laser output device. The laser output device comprises a laser, a beam expander, an acoustic optical modulator and a scanning head; the beam expander is used for expanding the diameter of a laser beam output by the laser; the input end of the acousto-optic modulator is connected with the output end of the beam expander; the input end of the scanning head is connected with the output end of the acoustic optical modulator; the acousto-optic modulator comprises an acousto-optic crystal, a collimator and a frequency adjusting module, the laser beam with the diameter expanded by the beam expander enters the acousto-optic crystal, the acousto-optic crystal outputs first-order diffraction light and zero-order diffraction light, the first-order diffraction light is output to the scanning head after passing through the collimator, the frequency adjusting module is connected with the acousto-optic crystal, and the zero-order diffraction light is output to the scanning head after passing through the collimator. The frequency adjusting module is used for adjusting the frequency of the laser beam in the acousto-optic crystal, so that the frequency of the first-order diffraction light is larger than the frequency of the laser beam entering the acousto-optic crystal. The laser output device can reduce the heat effect of the laser and improve the transmission efficiency of the laser.

column12: Test method for permeation rate of gel cement slurry
column13: The invention discloses a test method for the permeation rate of gel cement slurry. The test method sequentially comprises the following steps: (1) preparing cement slurry and testing a static gel strength curve SGS (t) of the cement slurry; (2) calculating the permeation rate of the cement slurry after the cement slurry is fixed for 10 minutes; (3) applying pressures to the two ends of a cement slurry column for leak-off of the cement slurry; (4) determining the average leak-off rate and the permeation rate of the cement slurry; (5) testing the corresponding permeation rate of hardened cement; (6) obtaining an initial permeation rate curve of the gel cement slurry; (7) correcting a result by the static gel strength curve SGS (t) to obtain the corrected permeation rate of the gel cement slurry. According to the test method, the performances of liquid cement slurry, the gel cement slurry and hardened cement are integrated, a principle is reliable, the operation is convenient, a relation between time and the gel transition-state permeation rate changed with the time in a solidifying process of the cement slurry can be determined, a scientific basis is provided for evaluating the anti-fluid-channeling capability of the cement slurry, and the application prospect is wide.

column12: Sectioned combination-type wind-deflection-preventing composite insulating inhaul cable and installation method
column13: Disclosed is a sectioned combination-type wind-deflection-preventing composite insulating inhaul cable including high-voltage-side hardware fittings, an upper rod body, a lower rod body and a middle pole. The upper end of the upper rod body and the lower end of the lower rod body are each connected with a high-voltage-side hardware fitting. The middle pole is connected between the upper rod body and the lower rod body. Each of the upper rod body and the lower rod body includes a rod core and an umbrella skirt at the outer side of the rod core. The rod cores are epoxy-resin glass-fiber-reinforced-plastic pulling rods. The umbrella skirts are silicone-rubber composite umbrella skirts. The cable is capable of preventing effectively deflection of wires, relative to a pole tower under the action of strong wind and preventing wind-deflection trip of lines so that safe operation level of power transmission lines is improved.

column12: Airport control behavior simulation method based on scene network resource dynamic locking
column13: The invention provides an airport control behavior simulation method based on scene network resource dynamic locking, and the method comprises the steps: constructing an airport scene network model, forming normalized airport scene structure data based on the airport scene network model, achieving the digital expression of a network topology relation between airport scene elements, and setting a scene operation rule. And generating simulation plan data, starting simulation, simulating machine position distribution, runway distribution and sliding path distribution behaviors based on a set scene operation rule, and carrying out resource dynamic locking and unlocking by taking a key point of a taxiway and a bidirectional sliding road section as focuses. A control behavior instruction is generated based on the real-time resource request of the aircraft and the state of the requested resource, and control behavior modeling simulation of the taxiing process is achieved. The method is more suitable for an actual control behavior mode, and can be applied to airport flight area operation simulation evaluation and airport scene automatic control.

column12: Intelligent mailbox
column13: An intelligent mailbox includes a mailbox, a sensor, a controller and a transmission unit. The mailbox has a containing space and a letter-taking opening. The containing space is configured to contain a letter, and the letter-taking opening is communicated with the containing space. The sensor is disposed in the mailbox and adjacent to the letter-taking opening. The sensor is configured to detect the letter in the containing space. The sensor generates a letter incoming signal when detecting the letter. The controller is disposed in the mailbox and connected to the sensor. The controller is configured to generate a letter incoming message according to the letter incoming signal. The transmission unit is configured to transmit the letter incoming message to a mobile device via wireless transmission. The intelligent mailbox can automatically detect incoming and taking letters and has a warning function, thereby improving convenience, practicability and security.

column12: Rocket modal parameter measurement method and system
column13: The invention discloses a rocket modal parameter measurement method and system, and relates to the technical field of rocket testing. The method comprises the steps: S1, selecting any cabin section connection surface of a rocket, and calculating N bending moments borne by the cabin section connection surface according to the loads borne by N characteristic moments in the flight process of the rocket; s2, N groups of rocket modal test horizontal suspension parameters corresponding to the cabin section connecting surface are determined according to the N bending moments borne by the cabin section connecting surface, and the rocket modal test horizontal suspension parameters comprise the number of suspension points, the positions of the suspension points and the tension of the suspension points; and S3, horizontally suspending the rocket for N times according to the N groups of rocket modal test horizontal suspension parameters of the cabin section connecting surface, and measuring the rocket modal parameters of the cabin section connecting surface in the N-time horizontal suspension state. When the modal parameters of the rocket are measured, the bending moment load borne by the butt joint surface of the selected cabin section is close to the bending moment load of the actual flight of the rocket, so that the modal parameter measurement precision of the rocket is high, and the measurement cost is low.

column12: Scheduling emergency knowledge management method based on natural language processing
column13: The invention provides a scheduling emergency knowledge management method based on natural language processing. The method comprises the following steps: S1, obtaining and preprocessing a scheduling emergency knowledge text; s2, performing word segmentation and annotation on the scheduling emergency knowledge text; s3, performing semantic classification and recognition on the dispatching emergency knowledge text; and S4, performing semantic analysis on the scheduling emergency knowledge text, extracting effective information and semantic component types thereof in the scheduling emergency knowledge text, and generating objectified information which can be identified by a computer. The system can improve the power grid dispatching emergency management level, automatically track the power grid state change, assist regulation and control personnel in understanding and mastering the real-time operation state of a power system, ensure the safe and stable operation of the power grid, effectively realize the automatic verification and control of power grid equipment, reduce the limitation and danger of the system, accurately recognize power grid control instructions input manually or imported in other modes, and improve automation, intelligence and interaction capability of power grid control.

column12: Novel construction auxiliary beam
column13: The utility model relates to the technical field of construction auxiliary beams, in particular to a novel construction auxiliary beam which comprises a base, two supports are installed at the upper end of the base, evenly-distributed installation cross beams are installed between the two supports, and evenly-distributed installation mechanisms are installed on the surfaces of the supports. By arranging the installation mechanism, after a worker installs two fixing sleeves on the surfaces of two adjacent nuts respectively, the two nuts can be mutually restrained through the fixing sleeves, the installation sleeves, the connecting square pipes and the connecting square rods to prevent the nuts from loosening, so that the stability of the construction auxiliary beam is improved, and the construction auxiliary beam is more convenient to use. In addition, the frequency of maintaining the construction auxiliary beam by workers can be reduced, the workers can work more easily, the good anti-loosening effect is achieved, and the workers can adjust the length, extending out of the connecting square pipe, of the connecting square rod according to the distance between every two adjacent nuts so as to meet the requirements of the nuts with different distances.

column12: Method for improving impact performance of Q355 round steel
column13: The invention discloses a method for improving impact performance of Q355 round steel. The method comprises the following steps that S1, material preparation stage is performed, specifically, S11, molten iron is processed, the molten iron is processed to enable the content of partial elements in the molten iron to reach the following standards that Si is smaller than and equal to 0.60%, S is smaller than and equal to 0.030% and P is smaller than and equal to 0.150%, and the temperature of the molten iron is controlled to enable the temperature of the molten iron to be not lower than 1250 DEG C; S12, scrap steel is processed, high-quality scrap steel is selected; S13, a converter is processed, the converter with the good converter condition is selected for use, and if water leakage of a smoke hood and an oxygen lance, large-area converter fettling and the like occur, smelting cannot be conducted; and S14, alloy is processed, medium-carbon ferromanganese, silicon-manganese alloy and the like are selected. According to the method for improving the impact performance of the Q355 round steel, the low-temperature plasticity of the steel grade is improved by reducing the content of C, Si, P and S in the molten steel, then the low-temperature impact performance of the steel grade is improved, the mechanical performance of the Q355 round steel is guaranteed by increasing the content of the Mn element in the molten steel, and meanwhile, the low-temperature impact performance of the Q355 round steel is improved by reducing the oxygen content in the Q355 round steel and inclusions in molten steel.

column12: Combined type wall connecting piece device for fixing overhanging type scaffold
column13: The utility model discloses a combined type wall connecting piece device for fixing an overhanging type scaffold, relates to the technical field of constructional engineering, and aims to solve the technical problems that after an existing external scaffold wall connecting piece is dismantled, a hole needs to be repaired in the later period, and the leakage risk is likely to happen. In the combined type wall connecting piece device for fixing the overhanging type scaffold, a fastener connected with a steel pipe is fixed through a connecting screw, and the fastener is fixedly connected with a double-layer plastic embedded pipe; the upper end of the fastener is provided with a first reserved bolt hole, the first reserved bolt hole is connected with an upper end screw rod, and the upper end screw rod is fixedly connected with a first nut at the upper end part; the lower end of the fastener is provided with a second reserved bolt hole, the second reserved bolt hole is connected with a lower end screw rod, and the lower end screw rod is fixedly connected with a second nut at the lower end part; meanwhile, the double-layer plastic embedded pipe embedded in the wall face in advance is fixedly connected with the upper end screw rod and the lower end screw rod through the first nut and the second nut.

column12: Steel bar machining line on construction site
column13: The utility model relates to a reinforcing steel bar machining line on a construction site. The device comprises a guide rail with scales along the line, reinforcing steel bar machining equipment capable of moving and being locked along the guide rail, supports arranged between the head end of the guide rail and the adjacent reinforcing steel bar machining equipment, and a stacking frame located on one side of the support at the head end of the guide rail and used for stacking reinforcing steel bars. The reinforcing steel bar machining equipment comprises a cutting machine and a bending machine, conveying rollers are arranged on the top faces of the stacking frame and the supports, reinforcing steel bars directly enter the supports arranged at the head ends of the guide rails after movingalong the conveying rollers on the stacking frame, and the reinforcing steel bars can be transferred between the reinforcing steel bar machining equipment when moving along the conveying rollers on the supports. According to the machining line, the operation intensity of workers during feeding and transferring is reduced, the operation safety is guaranteed, the machining quality and efficiency areimproved, and batch and standardization of steel bar machining are achieved.

column12: Asphalt paving and compacting machine head
column13: The utility model relates to the technical field of asphalt paving and compacting, in particular to an asphalt paving and compacting machine head which comprises an installation frame, a roller compacting mechanism, a paving assembly, a first lifting frame and a second lifting frame. The roller compacting mechanism comprises a roller support and a roller which is rotatably fixed on the roller support; The first lifting frame is connected between the roller support and the installation frame, the paving assembly is connected to the front portion of the roller compacting mechanism in a lifting mode through the second lifting frame. The asphalt paving and compacting machine head integrates the compaction function and the paving function and is installed on other walking vehicles of an asphaltthermal regeneration vehicle, the multi-point paving and compacting device can be flexibly and efficiently applied to small-range multi-point paving and compacting work in the pavement maintenance process, manual paving is replaced, the labor intensity of workers is reduced, and the labor efficiency and the production efficiency are improved.

column12: Power transmission line sag monitoring device based on UWB positioning technology
column13: The utility model discloses a power transmission line sag monitoring device based on the UWB positioning technology, and the device comprises a UWB base station disposed on a power transmission line iron tower, a movable monitoring unit which is disposed on a power transmission line and slides along the power transmission line, and a UWB label which is disposed on the movable monitoring unit and is in communication connection with the UWB base station. The activity monitoring unit comprises a shell; wherein the shell is suspended on a power transmission line through a sliding seat arranged atthe top of the shell, and a wire passing hole matched with the power transmission line is formed in the sliding seat; the image collector and the UWB label are mounted at the top of the sliding seat;the front end and the rear end of the shell are each provided with a micro air heater. Air blowing openings of the two micro air heaters face the power transmission lines on the front side and the rear side of the shell correspondingly. A first controller electrically connected with the UWB label, the image collector and the two micro air heaters, an environment monitoring assembly and a first wireless communication module are arranged in the shell, wherein the environment monitoring assembly and the first wireless communication module are electrically connected with the first controller. TheUWB base station is connected with a second controller, and the second controller is connected with a second wireless communication module.

column12: Width web plate device for splicing T-shaped beams of new and old bridges
column13: The utility model discloses a new and old bridge T beam widening web device which comprises a first T beam (1) and a second T beam (2), a first transverse plate (21) and a second transverse plate (22) are arranged between the two T beams, a buffer device is arranged on the first transverse plate (21) and comprises a first supporting rod (31), a compression spring (4) is arranged on the first supporting rod (31) in a sleeved mode, and the compression spring (4) is connected with the first supporting rod (31) in a sleeved mode. A supporting rod (24) is further arranged on the second supporting rod (32). The two transverse plates are arranged between the two T-beams, and the supporting rods, the supporting rods and the compressed springs are arranged between the two transverse plates, so that the rigidity and the stability of the bridge superstructure are improved, the load distribution of the two T-beams is more uniform, the structure is simple and compact, and the installation and the construction are convenient.

column12: Brake for large-scale machines
column13: A brake for large-scale machines comprises a hanging beam, an upper wrench body, a lower wrench body, friction plates, a mounting seat, return springs, a spiral lifter, a disc spring compression rod, a lever and a connecting rod, wherein the friction plates are positioned between the upper wrench body and the lower wrench body; the hanging beam is positioned in the middle of the electric wrench type brake, and two ends of the hanging beam are fixed at the top ends of uprights respectively; the uprights are sleeved by the return springs; the spiral lifter is mounted on one side of the hanging beam; the disc spring compression rod is positioned in the middle of the upper wrench body; one end of the lever is connected onto the upper wrench body in a twisted manner; the other end of the lever is connected with one end of the connecting rod in a twisted manner; the other end of the connecting rod is connected with a lead screw in a twisted manner; and the connecting rod is mounted on the upper surface of the upper wrench body through connecting lugs on the surface of the upper wrench body. As the abrasion of the friction plates can be automatically compensated, the brake for large-scale machines has the characteristics of low energy consumption, small volume and convenience in use and is suitable for the braking of large-scale machines.

column12: Asphalt paving and compacting machine head feeding device
column13: An asphalt paving and compacting machine head feeding device relates to the technical field of asphalt paving and compacting operation and comprises a hinged frame, a supporting sleeve, a movable arm, a movable arm push-pull oil cylinder and a supporting sleeve rotating oil cylinder, the supporting sleeve is horizontally and rotatably hinged to the hinged frame, the movable arm penetrates through the supporting sleeve in a front-back sliding mode, and the movable arm push-pull oil cylinder is connected with the supporting sleeve rotating oil cylinder. column12: Wind turbine blade leading edge protective coating and preparation method thereof
column13: The invention discloses a wind turbine blade leading edge protective coating and a preparation method thereof. The preparation method comprises the steps: in parts by weight, mixing 7-8 parts of nanotitanium dioxide, 1-2 parts of nano cerium oxide, 1 part of acrylic resin and 6 parts of water and carrying out ball milling to obtain functional filler dispersion liquid; and uniformly stirring 1 part of the silicon resin prepolymer, 1 part of the functional filler dispersion liquid and 5-15 parts of the polytetrafluoroethylene emulsion to obtain the wind turbine blade leading edge protective coating. The coating disclosed by the invention has the weather resistance of a ceramic coating and the toughness of resin, and is wear-resistant and strong in hydrophobicity. Meanwhile, the preparationmethod of the coating disclosed by the invention is composed of common industrial production processes, the process is simple, large-scale production is easy to realize, and the coating has a wide application prospect in the aspect of wind turbine blade leading edge protection.

column12: Method for loading optimization and monomerization of live-action three-dimensional model in game engine
column13: The invention discloses a method for loading optimization and monomerization of a live-action three-dimensional model in a game engine, and the method comprises the steps: selecting multi-level details for an oblique photography file format osgb, and displaying the level; judging the display level; removing non-selected levels, retaining the selected levels, performing traversing to obtain vertexcoordinates and material information, calculating model details and user distances, judging whether the model details and the user distances are within the sight distance or not, removing model fileswhich are not within the sight distance, retained and rendered within the sight distance and are associated according to MTL files, and exporting FBX format model files or map files. According to themethod and the system, the batch importing of the live-action three-dimensional models into the game engine is realized, and the data volume is also reduced; the monomeric display effect of ground objects is achieved, loading of two-dimensional GIS data is not needed, and loss of system performance is greatly reduced; feature extraction is carried out on the autonomously selected multi-level detail model, and extracted features are matched, so the influence of data redundancy is reduced, and the accuracy and efficiency of model conversion are improved.

column12: Manufacturing method for semiconductor diamond-like carbon film
column13: Disclosed is a manufacturing method for semiconductor diamond-like carbon film, in which a radio frequency magnetron sputtering method is used to fabricate boron-doped diamond-like carbon (B-DLC) film on silicon substrate, where the boron tablet is embedded in the graphite target as a composite target and the boron tablet is the doping source. After the boron-doped diamond-like carbon film is formed, the film is annealed at 500 degrees Celsius for 10 minutes, and then Hall effect and four-point probe analysis are performed to analyze its carrier density and resistance rate respectively. It is proven that the polarity of the boron-doped diamond-like carbon film is the p-type semiconductor characteristics, and the carrier density can be as high as 1.3 *10<SP>18 </SP>cm<SP>-3</SP> and the resistance rate is around 0.6 Ω-cm; therefore, the boron-doped diamond-like carbon film of this invention has excellent semiconductor characteristics and high-temperature stability, and will have superior applications and developments on solar cell or electronic transmission, and electrode elements and equipments.

column12: Rotatable intelligent centralizer
column13: The invention relates to a rotatable intelligent centralizer. The rotatable intelligent centralizer comprises a body, a baffle ring, a centralizing sleeve, a fixing sleeve and a locking ring, whereinthe centralizing sleeve is arranged on a boss structure of the body in a sleeving mode, a key connection structure is arranged on the inner wall of the centralizing sleeve, and rolling bearings, thrust bearings and sealing rings are arranged at the positions, on the two sides of the key connection structure, between the centralizing sleeve and the body; and the key connection structure is driven by a driving mechanism to rotate, the baffle ring sleeves one end of the body with a larger outer diameter, the fixing sleeve sleeves the body and is in sealing contact with the other side of the centralizing sleeve, the locking ring is fixedly connected with the body in a sealing mode and is in sealing contact with the fixing sleeve, an annular structure is formed among the centralizing sleeve, the fixing sleeve, the locking ring and the body, and the driving mechanism and a control module are positioned in the annular structure. By means of the intelligent control centralizer, the centralizercan be excited to rotate when a tubular column is lowered, friction between the tubular column and a well wall is reduced, meanwhile, turbulent flow is generated through rotation of the centralizer during well cementation, the cement paste displacement efficiency can be improved, and the well cementation quality is improved.

column12: Solar water heater with thermal/electric energy conversion
column13: A solar water heater with thermal/electric energy conversion comprises a solar heat collection module, a power generation module, a water storage device, and a heating medium operation piping module. The solar heat collection module absorbs and converts sunlight into thermal energy. The power generation module comprises a Stirling engine, a power generator that is driven by the Stirling engine to generate electrical power, and a power storage unit electrically connected to the power generator. The heating medium operation piping module is arranged in the solar heat collection module and connected to the Stirling engine and the water storage device to use the heating medium contained therein to absorb the thermal energy generated by the solar heat collection module and to make heat exchange with the Stirling engine and the water storage device. Besides heating the stored water, the present invention allows conversion of excessive thermal energy into electrical energy for other uses.

column12: METHOD FOR AUTOMATICALLY CONVERTING HIGH-LEVEL PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE INTO EAD
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a method for automatically converting a high-level programming language into an extended activity diagram (EAD).

SOLUTION: When converting mainly a high-level programming language (Java(R), C, C++ or the like) into a hardware description language, first of all, a source code of a program written in the high-level programming language is converted into an activity diagram. A compiler adds a new conversion rule, corrects an activity diagram specification in a UML, and converts the source code of the program into a corresponding activity diagram. Thus, a program logic of the source code and an execution process are expressed by a visualization system.

column12: CONTACT STRUCTURE WITH AIR SPACER FOR SEMICONDUCTOR DEVICE AND METHOD FOR FORMING THE SAME
column13: A method of forming a semiconductor device structure is provided. The method includes forming an insulating layer over a semiconductor substrate including a conductive feature, forming an insulating layer with a trench over the semiconductor substrate to expose the conductive feature, and forming a sacrificial liner layer over two opposite sidewalls and a bottom of the trench. Ions are implanted into the conductive feature covered by the sacrificial liner layer, so that a doping region is formed in the conductive feature and has two opposite side edges respectively separated from the two opposite sidewalls of the trench. The sacrificial liner layer is removed after forming the doping region, and a conductive connecting structure is formed in the trench. The two opposite sidewalls of the conductive connecting structure are respectively separated from the two corresponding opposite sidewalls of the trench by an air spacer.

column13: Ein Verfahren zur Halbleiterfertigung enthält das Bereitstellen einer Halbleiterstruktur, die ein Substrat und erste, zweite, dritte und vierte Finnen über dem Substrat aufweist. column12: Method and system for calculating power transmission capacity of extra-high voltage direct current layered access system
column13: The invention discloses a power transmission capacity calculation method and system for an extra-high voltage direct current layered access system, and the method comprises the steps: carrying out the state sampling of all equipment in the system through employing a non-sequential Monte Carlo method according to the effective sample capacity of a calculation error, and carrying out the combined solving of an alternating current and direct current hybrid power grid model and a power flow equation after the state of the equipment is determined, calculating the power flow of the selected equipment state; changing the operation state of the system by adjusting the generated output and the load demand, evaluating the operation state according to the position of the operation state in the multi-dimensional power injection space and the relative relationship between the operation state and the dynamic security domain, and when the operation state is evaluated to be normal, calculating the power flow based on alternate iteration to obtain the available transmission capability under the selected equipment state; and calculating the power transmission capability of the extra-high-voltage direct-current layered access system by using the statistical values of the various indexes of the available transmission capability sampled for multiple times in different equipment states. According to the method, the maximum power transmission capacity is calculated under different working conditions and different constraint conditions when extra-high voltage direct current is added in a layered mode.

column13: The invention relates to the technical field of asphalt paving and compacting, in particular to an asphalt feeding, paving and compacting integrated device which comprises a hinge frame, a supportingsleeve, a movable arm, a movable arm push-pull oil cylinder, a supporting sleeve rotating oil cylinder, a mounting frame, a roller compacting mechanism, a paving assembly, a first lifting frame and asecond lifting frame. column12: Motor driving system body type function safety test method and device
column13: The invention provides a motor driving system body type function safety test method and device. column12: Rail type permanent closing float collar
column13: The utility model relates to a track type permanent closing float collar which comprises a rubber plug, a float collar body and an inner sleeve, the closing sleeve, the float collar body and the inner sleeve are all of a hollow tubular structure, the closing sleeve is of a tubular structure with one end closed, a plurality of irregular track grooves are formed in the outer wall of the closing sleeve in the circumferential direction, and a plurality of circulation holes are formed in the side wall of the side, close to the closed end. The inner sleeve is installed on the inner wall of the float collar body, and the side wall of the inner sleeve is provided with a rail transfer pin matched with the non-shaped rail groove. At the initial position, the closing sleeve is fixed to the inner wall of the inner sleeve through a pin, the rail transfer pin is located in a short groove of the intangible rail groove, and the circulating hole is not blocked by the inner wall of the inner sleeve. When the rubber plug is pressed against the closing sleeve, the closing sleeve can move downwards to cut off the pin, the closing sleeve moves upwards under the action of counter pressure, the rail transfer pin enters the long groove of the intangible rail groove, and the circulating hole is blocked by the inner wall of the inner sleeve. The utility model has the advantages of simple structure and simplified field use process, and greatly improves the operation efficiency and the construction safety.

column12: Protection device intelligent patrol system based on multielement perception technology
column13: The invention discloses a protection device intelligent patrol system based on a multielement perception technology, which comprises an equipment perception layer, a network interconnection layer, an analysis application layer and a platform sharing layer, and is characterized in that the equipment perception layer comprises an infrared camera and a multielement perception device; the network interconnection layer comprises a station control layer center switch, a hard disk video recorder and an intelligent local module; the analysis application layer comprises an image recognition host and a secondary intelligent inspection device; and the platform sharing layer comprises a cloud platform and an adjusting and control system. According to the protection device intelligent patrol system based on the multielement perception technology, information of different dimensions can be integrated and used for discovering abnormity of equipment and a loop, early warning is carried out, rapid response to defects of a protection device and accurate positioning of hidden dangers are achieved, the patrol work efficiency of secondary equipment is improved, and unmanned or few-person patrol is really realized.

column12: Floating bridge capable of being opened horizontally
column13: The invention provides a floating bridge capable of being opened horizontally. The floating bridge is symmetrically arranged, and one side of the floating bridge sequentially comprises a fixed trestle section, a transition span bridge section and a movable floating bridge section; the fixed trestle section is fixed through a pier, and one end of the fixed trestle section is connected with a river bank through a bridge abutment; the transition span bridge section is connected between the fixed trestle section and the movable floating bridge section; an end fixing frame is arranged at the end of the movable floating bridge section, the end is connected with the transition span bridge section, fixation is performed through an anchoring assembly, and the movable floating bridge section is opened or closed through a driving device; and a middle gangplank is arranged between the movable floating bridge sections which are oppositely arranged, and the middle gangplank is rotatably connected to any one of the movable floating bridge sections. The floating bridge is simple in structure, low in operation and maintenance cost, high in adaptability and capable of meeting the requirement for multiple times of opening or closing of navigable water areas.

column12: Semiconductor device structure and method of forming the same
column13: An interconnect fabrication method is disclosed herein that utilizes a disposable etch stop hard mask over a gate structure during source/drain contact formation and replaces the disposable etch stop hard mask with a dielectric feature (in some embodiments, dielectric layers having a lower dielectric constant than a dielectric constant of dielectric layers of the disposable etch stop hard mask) before gate contact formation. An exemplary device includes a contact etch stop layer (CESL) having a first sidewall CESL portion and a second sidewall CESL portion separated by a spacing and a dielectric feature disposed over a gate structure, where the dielectric feature and the gate structure fill the spacing between the first sidewall CESL portion and the second sidewall CESL portion. The dielectric feature includes a bulk dielectric over a dielectric liner. The dielectric liner separates the bulk dielectric from the gate structure and the CESL.

column12: Semiconductor device and method
column13: In an embodiment, a method includes: forming a differential contact etch stop layer (CESL) having a first portion over a source/drain region and a second portion along a gate stack, the source/drain region being in a substrate, the gate stack being over the substrate proximate the source/drain region, a first thickness of the first portion being greater than a second thickness of the second portion; depositing a first interlayer dielectric (ILD) over the differential CESL; forming a source/drain contact opening in the first ILD; forming a contact spacer along sidewalls of the source/drain contact opening; after forming the contact spacer, extending the source/drain contact opening through the differential CESL; and forming a first source/drain contact in the extended source/drain contact opening, the first source/drain contact physically and electrically coupling the source/drain region, the contact spacer physically separating the first source/drain contact from the first ILD.

column12: Video matching method and infringement evidence storage method and device based on block chain
column13: The invention discloses a video matching method and an infringement evidence storage method and device based on a block chain. The infringement evidence storage method based on the block chain comprises the steps of acquiring multiple feature vectors of a target video; retrieving candidate videos similar to the target video from a video database based on the plurality of feature vectors of the target video; constructing a time domain similarity matrix feature map between the target video and the candidate video based on the target video and the candidate video; taking the time domain similarity matrix feature map as input of a deep learning detection model so as to output video clips matched with the target video in the candidate videos and corresponding similarities; and when the similarity is greater than or equal to a preset similarity threshold, uploading the abstract containing the target video, the video clip matched with the target video in the candidate video and the infringement evidence of the corresponding similarity to a block chain.

column12: Method for converting hardware component graph to hardware description language
column13: The present invention relates to an method for converting hardware component graph (HCG) into hardware description language (HDL), which can automatically generate codes of Very High Speed Integrated Circuit Hardware Description Language (VHDL). The method includes steps of reading a HCG to find a start node and obtain a corresponding hardware component subgraph of the start node, analyzing all information of the start node to thereby add input and output components and generate a VHDL entity, determining types of all nodes in the HCG to generate corresponding VHDL components and write associated information in a VHDL architecture, generating corresponding signal connections of VHDL components in accordance with edges of the HCG, and outputting the VHDL entity and architecture to a file in a form of character string.

column12: Method for testing and evaluating working condition efficiency of electric drive assembly of equivalent whole vehicle
column13: The invention provides a method for testing and evaluating the working condition efficiency of an electric drive assembly of an equivalent whole vehicle, and the method comprises at least one of the following steps: S1, carrying out the preparation before testing, and obtaining the parameters needed by the testing; s2, debugging a test bench and setting parameters according to the parameters required by the test and acquired in the step S1; s3, working condition efficiency testing is carried out, and test data are collected; and S4, working condition efficiency test results and evaluation are performed according to the test data in the step S3. The working condition efficiency testing method has the beneficial effects that from the design angle of the electric drive assembly, the output characteristics of the electric drive assembly can be associated with the actual working condition of the whole vehicle, and the method is beneficial to the research and development processes of performance parameters, control strategies, prototype calibration and the like of the electric drive assembly.

column12: Asphalt thermal regeneration paving and compacting vehicle
column13: The invention provides an asphalt thermal regeneration paving and compacting vehicle, relates to the technical field of asphalt road maintenance. column12: PERMEABLE METAL SUBSTRATE, METAL-SUPPORTED SOLID OXIDE FUEL CELL AND THEIR MANUFACTURING METHODS
column13: The invention provides a permeable metal substrate and its manufacturing method. The permeable metal substrate includes a substrate body and a permeable powder layer. The permeable powder layer is located on the top of the substrate body. The substrate body can be a thick substrate or formed of a thick substrate and a thin substrate that are welded together. Both the thick and thin substrates have a plurality of permeable straight gas channels. In addition, a metal-supported solid oxide fuel cell and its manufacturing method are also provided.

column12: Automatic analysis method of shield tunnel engineering and system thereof
column13: An automated analysis method of shield tunnel engineering is implemented on the management platform. First, input vehicle information and track geometric parameters, and generate envelope information based on the vehicle information and track geometric parameters. Then, the orbit information associated with the envelope information is generated. Then, upload or import the standardized form through the person in charge, the standardized form contains the geotechnical information. After that, perform segment design analysis and track design analysis based on track information and geotechnical information, and return parameter information to the standardized form. Finally, the modeling program creates a corresponding shield tunnel model based on the parameter information. In this way, a three-dimensional visual interface is provided to achieve application values such as the digitization of building information and the integration of professional illustrations. While avoiding the waste of resources, it also strengthens the management and control of cost, schedule, quality, etc.

column12: Method for automatically translating high level programming language into hardware description language
column13: The present invention is to provide a method for automatically translating a high level programming language into a hardware description language (HDL), which can use a three-stage translation mechanism to convert the functions described by the high level programming language into the corresponding HDL. The first stage translates source codes coded by the high level programming language into an extended activity diagram (EAD). The second stage translates the EAD into a hardware component graph (HCG). The third stage generates the respective signal connections of HDL components according to all edges of the HCG, and outputs an HDL entity and architecture to a file in a string form, thereby completing the entire translation.

column12: Portable quiescent temporary protecting device and application method
column13: The invention relates to a portable static temporary protecting device and an application method. The portable static temporary protecting device and the application method comprise a quiescent current relay, a quiescent time relay, a quiescent middle relay and a current loop pressing plate, wherein one end of the current loop pressing plate is connected with the quiescent current relay, and the other end of the current loop pressing plate is connected with the quiescent time relay and the quiescent middle relay. The portable static temporary protecting device and the application method have the advantages that the invention is suitable for 66 kilovolt (KV) 10KV transformer substations, the defects that wiring of a regular circuit breaker for temporary protection is complex, the type selection of a relay is difficult, and the accuracy is low are overcome, the work efficiency and operation safety of workers are improved, by switching the current loop pressing plate, a traditional temporary protecting function can be achieved, and also the quiescent temporary protecting function is achieved, and the wire connecting of connecting temporary protection is easy, convenient and safe.

column12: Voltage extracting apparatus
column13: The utility model relates to a voltage extracting apparatus. An inductive component of a voltage transformer is compensated by a capacitor. At a primary side of the voltage extracting apparatus, resistor elements are utilized as adjustment elements of secondary output voltage. A secondary side of the voltage extracting apparatus is connected with the loaded voltage transformer. The primary side is connected with an end screen of a current transformer. An adjustable resistor and a voltage-dividing resistor are connected in series and then respectively connected in parallel with a current-dividing resistor and the capacitor. The two ends of the capacitor are also connected in parallel with voltage stabilization elements. The voltage extracting apparatus is advantaged in that: system voltage is extracted through connecting with current of the end screen of the current transformer; input and output voltage of the voltage transformer is changed through adjusting the current-dividing resistor; output voltage exceeds extracted phase voltage for 90 degrees; and primary and secondary loop voltage of the voltage extracting apparatus is low so that running operations of equipment are safer and more reliable and the service life of elements is greatly prolonged.

column12: Automobile front face support installing and positioning device
column13: The utility model discloses an automobile front face support installing and positioning device which comprises a supporting frame horizontally attached to a water tank cross beam in the length direction of an automobile body, and a pair of longitudinal positioning pins matched with centering positioning holes in the top face of the water tank cross beam in an inserted mode are symmetrically arranged on the left side and the right side of the supporting frame. The rear end of the support frame is hinged with a pair of cross beam locking pieces which are longitudinally and rotatably propped against the bottom surface of the water tank cross beam; a sliding rail located above an automobile front face support is arranged at the front end of the supporting frame in a horizontally forward extending mode, a sliding base is arranged on the sliding rail, a pair of horizontal positioning pins used for clamping and fixing the automobile front face support is arranged on the lower portion of the sliding base, and a step-shaped positioning reference block used for clamping and supporting the front edge of an automobile engine hood is arranged on the sliding base located above the sliding rail.The positioning device has the advantages of being simple in structure, easy and convenient to operate and accurate in positioning, avoiding reworking and adjusting phenomena, reducing labor hour waste, reducing installation difficulty, reducing manpower and material resource consumption and greatly improving working efficiency of automobile assembly.

column12: High-efficiency bioreactor capable of realizing gas-liquid atomization
column13: The invention discloses a high-efficiency bioreactor capable of realizing gas-liquid atomization. The high-efficiency bioreactor comprises a main bioreactor body (1), gas deflectors (2), a three-phaseseparator (3), a discharge outlet (4), a gas outlet (5), a filtration system (6), a gas inlet (7), a liquid inlet (8), a gas-liquid mixer (9), an atomization system (10), a feed inlet (11), a liquiddistributor (12), a gas cabinet (13) and an external circulation system (14). The high-efficiency bioreactor capable of realizing gas-liquid atomization mainly adopts the principles of gas-liquid mixing and atomization to realize mixing and atomization of liquid and gas; after mixing and atomization, the gas and the liquid are jetted into the bioreactor, so the liquid and the gas can more fully contact with microorganisms in the bioreactor; and thus, mass transfer effect is enhanced, and the efficiency of the bioreactor is improved. The high-efficiency bioreactor is applicable as an aerobic aeration device, a device for reducing carbon dioxide with hydrogen, an airlift bioreactor, an expanded granular sludge bed reactor, an internal circulation reactor, a gas-stirring fully-mixing reactor,and the like.

column12: Method for recycling germanium and hydrogen chloride in germanium distillation tail gas through closed-loop circulation system
column13: The invention discloses a method for recycling germanium and hydrogen chloride in germanium distillation tail gas through a closed-loop circulation system. The means of first-stage falling film absorption, illumination, second-stage falling film absorption, bubble-cap tower interception and the like are adopted for germanium containing acid tail gas, the hydrogen chloride in the germanium distillation tail gas is subjected to falling film absorption, and germanium containing hydrochloric acid is formed, and returns to be used in a chlorination distillation manner, and hydrogen chloride tail gas generated in the distillation process is subjected to absorption to form hydrochloric acid; and the process is circulated in this way, chlorine is constantly and cyclically utilized in a productionsystem, and no waste water and waste gas of chlorine are generated. Meanwhile, germanium is recycled. A small amount of residual tail gas subjected to first-stage falling film absorption and second-stage falling film absorption is intercepted by a bubble-cap tower, layer-by-layer absorption is achieved from the tower bottom to the tower top, and about 1% acid waste water is generated and returns to a first-stage falling film absorption tower to be used as absorption liquid. All the tail gas is intercepted in the tower, and the effect of tail gas closed-loop circulation is achieved.

column12: Intelligent all-insulated AC screen
column13: The invention relates to an intelligent all-insulated AC screen which is characterized by comprising a cabinet body, an insulating board, a control unit, an electrical element, an exposed charged body, electrical meters and a controller, wherein the insulating board is arranged in the cabinet body and is used for sealing the electrical element and the exposed charged body in the cabinet body; the electrical meters and the controller are embedded into the insulating board; and the control unit is used for uploading the information in the cabinet body to a substation background system through a communication bus. The intelligent all-insulated AC screen has the advantages that a human-computer interface function is provided, on-site monitoring of the operating condition is realized, and the electrical quantity information of an AC power supply and the information of switching value can be all uploaded to the background system. The intelligent all-insulated AC screen can receive commands of the upper level for operation. The AC screen has the all-insulated characteristic, not only adopts earthing protection to avoid the electrification of the cabinet body, but also adopts an all-insulated structure to protect people from touching the charged body and being shocked.

column12: Five-coordinate machine tool comprehensive test pyramid type part and detection method
column13: The invention discloses a five-coordinate machine tool comprehensive test pyramid type part and detection method. The test pyramid type part comprises a base and a body, wherein the base is of a rectangular structure, the body is arranged on the base, the body comprises a first groove, a second groove unit and a chamfer, the first groove is formed in the center of the upper surface of the body, anarea of an opening of the upper end of the first groove is larger than that of the lower end of the first groove, and the center of the first groove is provided with a cylindrical boss; and the second groove unit is arranged at the center of the side surface of the body. column12: MCML retention flip-flop/latch for low power applications
column13: The present disclosure relates to a device and method to reduce the dynamic/static power consumption of an MCML logic device. In order to retain register contents during power off mode, an MCML retention latch and flip-flop are disclosed. Retention Latch circuits in MCML architecture are used to retain critical register contents during power off mode, wherein combination logic including clock buffers on the clock tree paths are powered off to reduce dynamic/static power consumption. The MCML retention flip-flop comprises a master latch and a slave latch, wherein a power switch is added to the master latch to power the master latch off during power off mode. The slave latch includes pull-down circuits that remain active to enable the slave latch to retain data at a proper voltage level during power off mode. Other devices and methods are also disclosed.

column12: MCML RETENTION FLIP-FLOP/LATCH FOR LOW POWER APPLICATIONS
column13: The present disclosure relates to a device and method to reduce the dynamic/static power consumption of an MCML logic device. In order to retain register contents during power off mode, an MCML retention latch and flip-flop are disclosed. Retention Latch circuits in MCML architecture are used to retain critical register contents during power off mode, wherein combination logic including clock buffers on the clock tree paths are powered off to reduce dynamic/static power consumption. The MCML retention flip-flop comprises a master latch and a slave latch, wherein a power switch is added to the master latch to power the master latch off during power off mode. The slave latch includes pull-down circuits that remain active to enable the slave latch to retain data at a proper voltage level during power off mode. Other devices and methods are also disclosed.

column12: Method for production of diamond-like carbon film having semiconducting property
column13: Method for production of diamond-like carbon film having semiconducting properties comprises preparing a boron-doped diamond-like carbon (B-DLC) thin film on a silicon substrate through a radio frequency magnetron sputtering process, wherein a composite target material formed by inserting boron tablet as a dopant source in a graphite target is used. After forming a boron-containing diamond-like carbon film, the thin film is annealed at a temperature of 500° C. and kept at this temperature for 10 minutes, and determine its carrier concentration and resistivity. Thus demonstrated that the polarity of said boron-doped diamond-like carbon film is p-type semiconductor characteristic. Carrier concentration can be up to 1.3×1018 cm-3, and its resistivity is about 0.6 Ω-cm; consequently. The boron-doped semiconducting diamond-like carbon film having excellent semiconductor property and high temperature stability according to the invention is best applicable in solar cell or electronic communication and electrode elements and equipments.

column12: Electric wire deicing device with telescopic structure for electric power operation and maintenance
column13: The invention relates to the technical field of electric wire deicing devices, in particular to an electric wire deicing device with a telescopic structure for electric power operation and maintenance. The electric wire deicing device with the telescopic structure for electric power operation and maintenance provided by the invention is handheld, an upper wire pressing wheel is used for limiting an electric wire, and a liftable deicing plate is matched to jack up the electric wire and compress the electric wire with the upper wire pressing wheel, so that the device is pulled to move along the trend of the electric wire, and the deicing plate can remove the ice coating. column12: Space trace gas detection positioning method and device based on narrow-band differential spectrometry
column13: The invention discloses a space trace gas detection and positioning method based on narrow-band differential spectroscopy, and relates to the technical field of GIS equipment monitoring, and the method comprises the following steps: generating an infrared thermal radiation light source through the infrared thermal radiation light source; detecting and positioning the SF6 leakage condition of the GIS equipment to obtain detection and positioning information; and the detection positioning information is received, processed, displayed and uploaded to a far-end monitoring platform. The invention discloses a space trace gas detection positioning device based on narrow-band differential spectrometry. According to the invention, SF6 gas leakage of the gas insulation high-voltage equipment is detected and positioned, trace gas leakage is found before a pressure gauge, and the position of a leakage point is indicated; the level of an existing SF6 gas leakage monitoring technology is greatly improved, and early-stage gas leakage of equipment can be found as soon as possible; the narrow-band differential spectrum is used for carrying out differential processing on the two paths of echo signals, so that the gas to be detected can be ensured to absorb enough light intensity, interference generated by other gases and the environment can be avoided, and accurate detection of SF6 gas micro leakage is realized.

column12: Non-shaft helix-integrated conveying type active simulated lunar soil conveying mechanism and test bed
column13: The invention discloses a non-shaft helix-integrated conveying type active simulated lunar soil conveying mechanism and a test bed, belonging to the technical field of lunar soil collection. Accordingto the active simulated lunar soil conveying mechanism and the test bed, the function of feeding size-variable graded simulated lunar soil in different filling velocities can be realized, and the technical problems that an existing selenographic comprehensive drilling test bed is low in utilization rate of simulated lunar soil and testing efficiency are solved. The active simulated lunar soil conveying mechanism comprises a conveying motor arranged below a raw material cylinder, wherein a spiral sleeve shaft is connected to the top end of the conveying motor, a non-shaft helix is mounted at the upper part of the spiral sleeve shaft; and a sleeve is arranged on the outer side of the lower part of the spiral sleeve shaft and is rotationally connected with the sleeve through a sealing device. The test bed comprises a full-parameter drilling mechanism, a coring mechanism and the active soil conveying mechanism. The active soil conveying mechanism has the beneficial effects that the lunarsoil is conveyed through the rotation of the non-shaft helix, the amount of the contained lunar soil is very small, and the time for preparing a large amount of the lunar soil is saved; the efficiencyis improved; the effect for conveying the lunar soil with relatively poor fluidity is obvious, and the soil conveying performance is good; and the active soil conveying mechanism is short in test period and high in efficiency, can meet experiment conditions under different working conditions and is easy to observe and analyze.

column13: The present invention provides a composition capable of facalitating the regeneration of articular cartilage and a method of repairing the articular cartilage by using the same. The composition of repairing articular cartilage contains platelet-rich fibrin releasate and stem cells and can be used to facilitate the regeneration of articular cartilage, so as to achieve the efficacy of preventing and curing arthritis.
