column12: Process of automatically translating a high level programming language into a hardware description language
column13: A process of automatically translating a high level programming language into a hardware description language (HDL), which can use a three-stage translation mechanism to generate the HDL codes corresponding to the functions described by the high level programming language. The first stage translates source codes coded by the high level programming language into an extended activity diagram (EAD). The second stage translates the EAD into a hardware component graph (HCG). The third stage generates the respective signal connections of HDL components according to all edges of the HCG, and outputs an HDL entity and architecture to a file in a string form, thereby completing the entire translation.

column12: Handheld auxiliary pressing tool
column13: The handheld auxiliary pressing tool comprises a pressing unit and an alarm unit, the pressing unit comprises a handheld cylinder, a fixing base and a pressing rod in sliding connection are installed in a containing cavity of the handheld cylinder, the lower end of the pressing rod is connected with a second spring in a sleeved mode and can penetrate through a center through hole of the fixing base, and the top end of the pressing rod extends out of the containing cavity and is provided with an installation sleeve. The device is ingenious in structure, convenient to use, easy to operate, energy-saving and environment-friendly, manual pressing force is replaced by spring elasticity, ideal pressing force is obtained by selecting a spring with a proper elasticity coefficient and a proper compression distance, and sound-light alarm is performed when the pressing state is optimal by combining a built-in alarm circuit. column13: The invention discloses a traceability-based Android mobile attack prevention method, which comprises the following steps of: performing first timing communication, and judging whether the first timing communication is in a smooth state or not; if the state is not smooth, obtaining first communication data; acquiring the position of a second server; disconnecting the communication network; when the reading of the timer is equal to the first numerical value, recovering the communication network, and judging whether the distance between the server and the second server meets the requirement of near field communication or not; if the near field communication requirement is met, obtaining second communication data; performing data comparison processing to obtain repeated data; inputting the repeated data into a first traceability model for processing to obtain a first traceability result; performing forbidding processing, and then judging whether the state is a smooth state or not; if the state is still not smooth, forming the network connection in the near field communication network, and and obtaining a second traceability result. By carrying out the precaution operation by adopting the precaution strategy, the attack traceability is more accurate and more hierarchical, and the attack precaution is more targeted.

column12: Multi-node cooperative computer virus analysis system
column13: The utility model discloses a multi-node cooperative computer virus analysis system, and belongs to the field of computer virus analysis. According to the utility model, analysis tasks are carried out through the plurality of analysis node devices, the monitoring module monitors task processing processes of the analysis node devices and uploads the task processing processes to the task management device through the second network switch, and the task management device manages the analysis tasks through the task processing processes of the plurality of nodes. In practical application, the management can redistribute tasks and reproduce the analysis node devices required to confirm the next analysis task. The virus analysis tasks of the multiple analysis node devices are managed through the task management device, so that the virus analysis efficiency can be improved, and reasonable utilization of resources of the multiple analysis node devices is achieved.

column12: Fault diagnosis method for circuit breaker operating mechanism on basis of CCA (Curvilinear Component Analysis)-SOM (Self-organizing Map)
column13: The invention discloses a fault diagnosis method for a circuit breaker operating mechanism on the basis of CCA (Curvilinear Component Analysis)-SOM (Self-organizing Map). The fault diagnosis method comprises the following steps: firstly establishing a fault diagnosis data model of the circuit breaker operating mechanism; then performing dimension reduction on characteristic quantity extracted from circuit breaker opening and closing coil current by utilizing a curvilinear component analysis algorithm; subsequently classifying fault types by utilizing a self-organizing neural network algorithm to obtain self-organizing neural network algorithm training results; finally performing fault diagnosis on to-be-tested circuit breaker opening and closing coil current data by utilizing the self-organizing neural network algorithm training results. The fault diagnosis method for the circuit breaker operating mechanism on the basis of CCA-SOM, disclosed by the invention, has the benefit that a curvilinear component analysis and self-organizing neural network is applied to the fault diagnosis of the circuit breaker operating mechanism, so that the diagnosis speed is high, and the diagnosis result accuracy rate is high.

column12: Reliability verification method, device and system based on computer forensics
column13: The invention discloses a reliability verification method, a device and a system based on computer forensics. The method comprises the steps of obtaining hidden computer viruses, an image recognition model and a coding rule; enabling visible light to irradiate a real picture frame; performing first image acquisition processing to obtain a first image, and obtaining a first image recognition result; performing first encoding processing to obtain a first code; enabling ultraviolet rays and visible light to irradiate the real picture frame at the same time; performing second image acquisition processing to obtain a second image, and obtaining a second image recognition result; obtaining a second code; enabling the real picture frame to be only irradiated by ultraviolet rays; performing third image acquisition processing to obtain a third image, and obtaining a third image recognition result; performing third encoding processing to obtain a third code; integrating into a total code, and calculating a similarity value; and if the similarity value is greater than the similarity threshold, judging that the computer evidence obtaining is reliable. Therefore, the reliability verification of evidence obtaining of the hidden computer viruses is realized.

column12: Distributed file protection system comprising multiple protection devices
column13: The utility model discloses a distributed file protection system comprising a plurality of protection devices, and belongs to the technical field of virus prevention. The communication connection between the network end and the file storage server is physically isolated before the file access request accesses the file, and the communication connection is recovered after the file access request is monitored to complement a malicious request or no virus is contained, so that the attack to the file in the monitoring process is avoided. The detection server and the distributed file storage server are separately arranged, so that physical isolation between the network side and the distributed file storage server is realized in the process of monitoring the file access request, the distributed file storage server is prevented from being attacked by viruses or malicious access requests in the detection process, and the safety of the distributed file storage server is improved. And the situation that a virus or a malicious access request bypasses a monitoring program and directly attacks the file is avoided, and the security of the file is improved.

column12: Unmanned aerial vehicle mechanical arm-based crane metal structure detection device and method
column13: The invention discloses an unmanned aerial vehicle mechanical arm-based crane metal structure detection device and method and belongs to the field of crane metal structure damage recognition. The device comprises an unmanned aerial vehicle main body, a ground treatment device, a mechanical arm, a non-destructive detection device and a camera. The unmanned aerial vehicle main body is used for carrying the mechanical arm and the non-destructive detection device. A non-destructive detection probe carried by the mechanical arm above the unmanned aerial vehicle main body contacts with the metal structure surface and acquires a defect characteristic signal, the defect characteristic signal is transmitted to the non-destructive detection device main body through a cable and then is transmitted to the ground treatment device through a wireless communication link, the ground treatment device carries out time-domain and frequency-domain analysis and constructs defect signal identification feature vectors, and an Euclidean distance of the feature vector between the signal to be detected and a known defect signal is calculated to determine a degree of approximation so that a signal defect type is identified. The device and method realize automatic detection and identification of defect features such as cracks, corrosion and holes on the metal structure surface and subsurface.

column12: APPARATUS FOR PROMOTING MARINE ALGA GROWTH BY IRRADIATION OF IONIZING RADIATION
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide an apparatus for promoting marine alga growth by irradiation of ionizing radiation.

SOLUTION: This apparatus for promoting marine alga growth includes pouring a culture solution into a placement area of a storage unit, implanting a plurality of algae spores into an attached unit, performing water flow culturing by a culture solution with a filter in the placement area, irradiating with a radiation irradiating unit, a dose required for an irradiation frequency section which is set with a time unit so as to grow each of the algae spores to algae young buds, taking away the algae young buds from the attached unit followed by setting in an outdoor water flow pond, performing water flow culturing, and further collecting algae from the attached unit after each of the algae grows to an appropriate length. Then, it is possible to promote alga growth by a hormesis method, find out the most suitable thickness increase or shortening of a growth period, and reproduce necessary algae in mass production.

column12: Steel corrugated plate composite structure for high fill or large span
column13: The invention relates to a steel corrugated plate composite structure for high filling or large span. The steel corrugated plate composite structure comprises an arc-shaped outer-layer steel corrugated plate and an arc-shaped inner-layer steel corrugated plate, wherein the arc-shaped outer-layer steel corrugated plate and the arc-shaped inner-layer steel corrugated plate are integrally formed by annularly lapping single steel corrugated plates which are produced in a standardized manner in a factory, splicing the single steel corrugated plates through high-strength bolts and then longitudinally splicing the single steel corrugated plates in a staggered-joint splicing manner. The two layers of steel corrugated plates are connected together through long bolts, the outer-layer steel corrugated plate and the inner-layer steel corrugated plate are connected with corresponding factory prefabricated and assembled concrete foundations through angle steel respectively, foam concrete is poured between the outer-layer steel corrugated plate and the inner-layer steel corrugated plate, an integral structure is formed, and then a waterproof layer is made. By adopting the flexible steel corrugated plate and the rigid concrete structure, the requirement of the steel corrugated plate bridge culvert for stress can be improved, the overall bearing capacity of the structure is improved, the problem that the structure is unstable due to the fact that the thickness of a high-fill and large-span steel corrugated plate cannot be achieved by a machining process is solved, standardized production is achieved, the construction period is shortened, and the construction cost is reduced. Mining of cement and sand is reduced, and environmental protection is facilitated.

column12: METHOD AND APPARATUS OF RFID TAG CONTACTLESS TESTING
column13: A semiconductor wafer includes a plurality of dies. Each of the plurality of dies includes a radio frequency identification (RFID) tag circuit and a coil. The RFID tag circuit includes a tag core, an RF front-end circuit, an ID decoder, a comparator and conductive line for a unique ID. The RF front-end circuit is configured to receive electromagnetic signals through the coil in each of the plurality of dies and to convert the received electromagnetic signals into commands. The ID decoder is configured to receive the commands and to generate an expect ID. The comparator is configured to compare the unique ID with the expect ID to generate a comparison result. The comparison result is arranged to decide if the tag core is configured to receive commands.

column12: Ammoniation method and device for polyacrylonitrile spinning solution
column13: The invention discloses an ammoniation method and device for a polyacrylonitrile spinning solution. The ammoniation method comprises the following steps: (1) quantitatively mixing an ammoniation reagent and a solvent to obtain a mixed solution with controllable ammonia content; (2) dispersing polyacrylonitrile powder into the mixed solution with controllable ammonia content prepared in the step (1), and uniformly stirring to obtain polyacrylonitrile slurry; (3) heating and dissolving the polyacrylonitrile slurry prepared in the step (2) to obtain a transparent and uniform polyacrylonitrile solution; and (4) carrying out defoaming treatment on the polyacrylonitrile spinning solution prepared in the step (3) to prepare the polyacrylonitrile spinning solution. Compared with an ammonia gas bubbling method and a solution polymerization method which are commonly adopted in the prior art, the ammoniation method for mixing the ammonia-containing solution and the polyacrylonitrile powder and then heating can flexibly adjust the polyacrylonitrile content in the spinning solution, the requirement of the spinning process for the pressure before spinning is met, and the spinning pressure caused by viscosity increase due to ammoniation is reduced; ammonia water is adopted for ammoniation treatment, so that the ammoniation degree can be controlled while full ammoniation reaction is ensured, and the method is suitable for popularization and application.

column12: HEPATITIS B THERAPEUTIC VACCINES
column13: A fusion protein for use as a hepatitis B therapeutic vaccine is disclosed. The fusion protein comprises: (a) an antigen-presenting cell (APC)-binding domain or a CD91 receptor-binding domain; (b) a protein transduction domain; and (c) an antigen comprising a hepatitis B virus X protein deletion mutant that lacks amino acids (aa) at least from aa 21 to aa 50. The protein transduction domain is a fusion polypeptide comprising a T cell sensitizing signal-transducing peptide, a linker, and a translocation peptide. The APC-binding domain or the CD91 receptor-binding domain is located at the N-terminus of the fusion protein, and the antigen is located at the C-terminus of the protein transduction domain.

column12: RADIOACTIVE As-CONTAINING COMPOUND AND USE OF THE SAME IN TUMOR TREATMENT
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a method for producing a radioactive As-containing compound and obtain a pharmaceutical composition containing the compound.

SOLUTION: The method for producing the radioactive As-containing compound comprises (i) a process for irradiating neutron to an As-containing compound (selected from the group consisting of As2O3, As2S3, As2S2and a combination of those) and converting As contained in the As-containing compound into a radioactive As isotope; and (ii) a process for collecting the resulted product from the process (i). The pharmaceutical composition containing a therapeutically effective amount of the radioactive As-containing compound and a pharmaceutically permissible support is prescribed to an injection formulation and used for treating tumors/cancers such as hematologically malignant tumors and solid tumors.

column12: Bird driving device for pole
column13: The invention relates to a bird driving device for a pole. The device comprises an electric shock mesh which is parallelly mounted on a cross arm of the pole, wherein the electric shock mesh comprises a support capable of being fixed on the cross arm, and low level transverse bars and high level transverse bars which are fixedly, alternately and parallelly arranged on the support in a staggered mode, a distance between the low level transverse bar and the high level transverse bar adjacent to the low level transverse bar is smaller than or equal to the largest dimension of expanded claws of a target bird, each low level transverse bar is respectively used for connecting with the ground, each high level transverse bar is respectively used for connecting a metal cap of an insulation string of the pole, and thereby an electric potential difference for driving the target bird is formed between the low level transverse bar and the high level transverse bar adjacent to the low level transverse bar. The bird driving device for the pole can effectively prevent the target bird from multiplying and inhabiting on a dangerous part of the pole for a long term, so power transmission line tripping accident frequency can be reduced, and the safe and stable operation level of a power transmission line can be improved.

column12: Device for helping seaweed growing by shinning ionizing radiation
column13: A device for helping the seaweed growing by shinning the ionizing radiation is disclosed. Cultivation liquid is poured in a placing area of a containing unit, and a plurality of algae spores on an adherence unit. And then using a filter, the cultivation liquid in the placing area is cultured in running water type. After that, a required dose is provided by illumination of the radiation unit, and shinning frequency range is set by a timing unit. When each alga spore initially grows into an algae seedling, the adherence unit is taken, putting in an outdoor running water pound to be cultured in running water type again. When each alga grows into a suitable length, the algae can be taken off from the adherence unit. Therefore, promoting its growing by radiation hormesis method to find the best increasing thickness or shorten the growing period to achieve the effect of producing and breeding the required seaweed in large scale.

column12: A bird repellent device for shaft tower
column13: The utility model relates to a bird repellent device for shaft tower, it is including can install the electric shock aperture plate on the cross arm of shaft tower parallelly. The electric shock aperture plate is including fixing the support on the cross arm, fixed parallel electronegative potential transverse strip and the high potential transverse strip who arranges in turn who sets up on the support. Wherein, the maximum size apart from the expansion bird claw of less than or equal to target bird between adjacent electronegative potential transverse strip and the high potential transverse strip, each electronegative potential transverse strip all is used for connecting the earth, and each high potential transverse strip all is used for connecting the insulator chain's of shaft tower metal cap for form the electrical potential difference that is used for driveing the target bird between adjacent electronegative potential transverse strip and the high potential transverse strip. The utility model discloses a bird repellent device for shaft tower can prevent for a long time, effectively that the target bird from multiplying and perch in the dangerous part of shaft tower to can reduce the number of times of transmission line tripping operation accident, improve transmission line's safety and stability and move the level.

column12: Establishment method for personal health assessment system
column13: The invention relates to an establishment method for a personal health assessment system. It comprises the following steps: establishing a health database; setting a disease theme; capturing main bodies associated with the disease theme from health data files of the health database to establish a thematic database; establishing a secondary database through a mode establishment and a variable reorganization establishment for archives within the thematic database; establishing a cloud query system through the result data of the secondary database. Thereby the expected assessment for the current and future risk status associated with users' diseases is provided to the users through a processing unit of the cloud query system on the basic of the result data of each secondary database when the users input their own health status from the cloud query system. Accordingly, it can help users manage personal health more effectively.

column12: Voltage phase sequence discrimination method and device based on electric energy data, medium and terminal
column13: The invention discloses a voltage phase sequence judgment method and device based on electric energy data, a medium and a terminal, relates to the field of electric power, and mainly aims to solve the problem that the risk of personal electric shock injury exists because metering personnel need to perform wiring operation in a field electrified metering loop in the prior art. The problems of open circuit of a secondary circuit of a current transformer, short circuit of a voltage circuit, damage of metering equipment, tripping of a circuit breaker and the like can be possibly caused to cause a large-area power failure accident risk of a power grid. Comprising the steps that electric energy data of all elements of a current circuit are acquired based on a three-phase three-wire intelligent electric energy meter, and the electric energy data comprise voltage data, current data, reactive power data and a power factor; respectively calculating an angle value of a voltage leading current of each element according to a power factor and reactive power data in the electric energy data of each element; and determining the voltage phase sequence of the current circuit according to the angle value of the voltage lead current of each element based on an assumption method.

column12: Method and system for detecting wrong wiring of Yn/Yn voltage transformer, medium and equipment
column13: The invention discloses a Yn/Yn voltage transformer false wiring detection method and system, a medium and equipment, and the method comprises the steps: constructing an equivalent phasor diagram of an intelligent electric energy meter, and the equivalent phasor diagram comprises a voltage phasor and a current phasor; determining voltage data of the intelligent electric energy meter corresponding to the voltage phasor; and determining that the intelligent electric energy meter has a voltage polarity reverse connection wiring fault based on the fact that the voltage data is located in a preset voltage range corresponding to the voltage phasor. Therefore, automatic wiring fault judgment is realized, the dependence of fault detection on the technical level of workers is reduced, the difficulty of fault judgment is greatly reduced, the efficiency of equipment fault diagnosis is improved, and metering personnel are assisted in positioning fault problems in time, so that electric power resources are accurately supervised. And meanwhile, workers do not need to perform wiring operation on a live metering loop on site, so that accidents such as personal electric shock injury and open circuit of a secondary loop of the current transformer are avoided.

column12: Intelligent substation communication network description model based on SDN
column13: The invention discloses an intelligent substation communication network description model based on an SDN. The model comprises an embedded model of the SDN in the intelligent substation communication network and an intelligent substation communication network architecture based on the SDN; the embedded model comprises an intelligent substation three-layer two-network structure, an SDN controller and an OpenFlow switch, and equipment participating in access of a process layer is a merging unit and an intelligent terminal; equipment accessed to the spacing layer is a protection device, a measurement and control device and a metering device. Equipment participating in access of the station control layer is a monitoring device and a telecontrol device. The communication network architecture comprises a data layer, a control layer and an application layer. The data layer comprises an SDN switch and a communication domain; the control layer comprises an SDN controller, a resource manager and network service; and the application layer comprises an SDN application, a terminal server and a user interface. According to the invention, the diversification requirements of communication between the intelligent substation and the terminal equipment are met by using the SDN technology, and multi-dimensional fine description of the communication system is realized.

column12: Radioactive arsenic-containing compounds and their uses in the treatment of tumors
column13: This invention provides a process for producing a radioactive arsenic-containing compound, comprising the steps of: (i) subjecting an arsenic-containing compound to a neutron irradiation treatment, said arsenic-containing compound being selected from a group consisting of As 2 O 3 , As 2 S 3 , As 2 S 2 , and a combination thereof, such that the arsenic element contained in the arsenic-containing compound is converted to a radioactive arsenic isotope; and (ii) recovering the resultant product from step (i). This invention also provides a pharmaceutical composition comprising a therapeutically effective amount of the radioactive arsenic-containing compound and a pharmaceutically acceptable carrier. The pharmaceutical composition can be used in the treatment of tumors/cancers such as hematological malignancies and solid tumors.

column12: PHARMACEUTICAL COMPOSITION CONTAINING THERAPEUTICALLY EFFECTIVE AMOUNT OF RADIOACTIVE ARSENIC-CONTAINING COMPOUND AND PHARMACEUTICALLY ACCEPTABLE CARRIER
column13: PURPOSE: A pharmaceutical composition containing a therapeutically effective amount of radioactive arsenic-containing compounds and a pharmaceutically acceptable carrier is provided. The composition can be used in the treatment of tumors/cancers such as hematological malignancies and solid tumors selected from a group consisting of breast cancer, rectal cancer, liver tumor, ovarian cancer and prostate cancer. CONSTITUTION: The pharmaceutical composition contains a therapeutically effective amount of radioactive arsenic-containing compounds and a pharmaceutically acceptable carrier. The radioactive arsenic-containing compounds are prepared by the steps of: (i)subjecting an arsenic-containing compound to a neutron irradiation treatment to convert an arsenic element contained in an arsenic-containing compound to a radioactive arsenic isotope; and (ii)recovering the resultant product. The arsenic-containing compound is selected from a group consisting of As2O3, As2S3, AS2S2, and a combination thereof. The radioactive arsenic-containing compound is neutron-irradiated arsenic trioxide, and is formulated into an aqueous injection formulation. The pharmaceutical composition is administered parenterally, orally, or topically in an amount of 0.01 to 0.6 mg/Kg of body weight per day, in single or multiple doses.

column12: Information network security early warning system for coping with continuous threat attack
column13: The invention discloses an information network security early warning system for coping with continuous threat attacks. The information network security early warning system comprises a user behavior data source module, a data acquisition and preprocessing module, a database subsystem, a user behavior analysis module, a feature extraction and modeling module, an anomaly detection and early warning module and an input and output interface module. According to continuous threat attack style characteristics, an artificial intelligence algorithm is used for extracting user behavior features, establishing a user behavior feature library and continuously performing self-optimization, so that automatic upgrading of a security early warning model is realized, effective early warning is performed for coping with continuous threat attacks, and the overall security protection level of an information network is effectively improved.

column12: Unmanned aerial vehicle inspection method with information security
column13: The invention discloses an unmanned aerial vehicle inspection method with information security, thereby solving a problem that in the prior art, unmanned aerial vehicle inspection information and dataare prone to being tampered and leaked. The system adopted by the invention comprises an inspection operation platform, an unmanned aerial vehicle, terminal equipment and a cloud database which are connected with the inspection operation platform. The unmanned aerial vehicle inspection method comprises the following steps: S1, selecting an authority identity to log in the inspection operation platform, setting different authority identities to have different operation authorities that are given by the superior through secret keys; S2, controlling the unmanned aerial vehicle to execute inspection work by using the inspection operation platform according to the authority; and S3, feeding back power grid operation data obtained by the inspection work to the inspection operation platform by the unmanned aerial vehicle, and carrying out analysis, warning, and responsibility claiming on the data. According to the method, a strict identity authority system is set, the authority is given through the secret key, so that invasion of the illegal personnel to the system is avoided, random tampering and leakage of data or information are prevented, and data safety is guaranteed to a great extent.

column12: AUTOMATIC CONVERSION METHOD OF HIGH-LEVEL LANGUAGE INTO HARDWARE DESCRIPTION LANGUAGE
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide an automatic conversion method of a high-level language into a hardware description language.

SOLUTION: In this automatic conversion method of a high-level language into a hardware description language, a function described in the high-level language is converted by a three-step conversion method, to thereby generate a corresponding hardware description language. In the first step, first of all, a source program code of the high-level language is converted into an extended activity diagram (EAD). Then, in the second step, the activity diagram is converted into a hardware component graph (HCG). Finally, in the third step, online based on the hardware component graph (HCG) causes signal connection of a corresponding VHDL component, and the entity and the architecture of VHDL are outputted into one file by a character string system, to thereby complete the whole conversion.

column12: Network security system based on honeypot technology
column13: The invention discloses a network security and protection system based on a honeypot technology. The network security and protection system comprises a software defined network control subsystem and a cheating server, the software defined network control subsystem comprises a virtual network topology module and an IP randomization module; the virtual network topology module is mainly responsible for generating a virtual network topology and distributing a flow table according to the specification of the virtual network topology; the IP randomization module is responsible for coordinating address transformation of a host and a bait node in a network; the spoofing server is responsible for making a response according to the specification of the virtual network view to spoofing the malicious scanning program. According to the method, the dynamic nature, the randomness and the uncertainty of the system are increased, so that an attacker spends more time on false resources, the attack difficulty and the attack cost of the attacker are further improved, the defense efficiency and the security of the system are effectively enhanced, and the method has the advantages that infrastructures for network system development and management are flexible and effective, the operation overhead is small, and the implementation is easy. And continuous network investigation attacks can be effectively resisted.

column12: Operation-maintenance automatic inspection method for fine granularity control and system thereof
column13: The invention discloses an operation-maintenance automatic inspection method for fine granularity control and a system thereof. The method comprises the following steps: S1, building a unified daily inspection knowledge base; S2, according to a business scene, generating an inspection task; S3, performing the scheduling execution to the inspection task in the step S2; and S4, generating an inspection report. The system comprises the inspection knowledge base. The inspection knowledge base is used for providing the equipment information and inspection index to an inspection task module, providing the collecting protocol and collecting script to an inspection task executing module, and providing the judgment standard to an inspection report module. The inspection task module is used for generating the inspection task. The inspection task executing module is used for automatically executing the inspection task in the inspection task module. The inspection report is used for presenting an inspection result in the manner of a report form. The requirement for the daily inspection can be satisfied, and the control of equipment access authority is guaranteed in the greatest degree.

column12: System module of simulating machine operation screen based on non-invasive data-extraction system
column13: A system module applied to the machine controller for simulating a machine operation screen based on a non-invasive data-extraction system, is disclosed. An image capture device of the system module can receive an original operation screen outputted from the machine controller, and transmit the original operation screen to the non-invasive data-extraction system and a high-speed image process unit for extraction of the information shown on the operation screen. The software control system can extract the operational information of the machine controller in real time, to create a machine operation flow for generating a simulated machine operation screen which is then outputted to a screen of the machine controller. column12: System module for simulating machine operation screen based on non-invasive data extraction system allowing a site working staff to obtain operational information associated with a machine in real time
column13: The present invention provides a system module for simulating machine operation screen based on a non-invasive data extraction system, which is applicable to a machine controller. An image capturing device of the system module can receive an original operation screen outputted from the machine controller, and transmit the original operation screen to a non-invasive data extraction system and a high-speed image processing unit for extraction of the information shown on the operation screen. As such, a software control system can extract the operational information of the machine controller in real time based on the configuration of the non-invasive data extraction system, so as to create a machine operation flow for generating a corresponding simulated machine operation screen which is then outputted to a screen of the machine controller by an image output device. In addition, through the assistance of the high-speed image processing unit, a site working staff can obtain operational information associated with the machine in real time, including a currently executed operation screen, a position of a mouse cursor and detection of a pop-up window. Furthermore, more accurate machine control procedures can be provided by using a signal receiving the device and a human-machine interface simulator.

column12: Pipe combining structure in cooling water passing bin for dam concrete pouring and method of pipe combining structure
column13: The pipe combining structure in the cooling water passing bins for dam concrete pouring comprises a plurality of dam sections, and is characterized in that seamless steel pipes are arranged at transverse joints among the dam sections along the axis of the dam, and the two ends of each seamless steel pipe are pre-buried in the corresponding dam section and communicated into the corresponding cooling water passing bin arranged in the corresponding dam section; the cooling water inlet pipe and the cooling water outlet pipe penetrate through the transverse seam between the dam sections through the seamless steel pipe and penetrate out of the dam body, and the intelligent water passing equipment is connected with the inlet end of the cooling water inlet pipe; one or more branch pipes for concrete pouring and cooling are arranged in each cooling water passing bin, one end of each branch pipe is connected with the cooling water inlet pipe, and the other end of each branch pipe is connected with the upstream cooling water outlet pipe. According to the method, the problems that in the prior art, a cooling water pipe is prone to breakage and water leakage, pressure is not enough, and the side face guide wall penetrating pipes are too many and too concentrated can be solved, and the stable, safe and attractive concrete pouring method is provided.

column12: Unmanned aerial vehicle landing optimization method and device based on image recognition
column13: The invention provides an unmanned aerial vehicle landing optimization method and device based on image recognition, and relates to the technical field of unmanned aerial vehicle landing, and the method comprises the steps: obtaining a two-dimensional code image, and obtaining the central point of the two-dimensional code image and the information of the two-dimensional code image; judging whether the central point of the two-dimensional code image is a parking point of the unmanned aerial vehicle to be landed or not based on the two-dimensional code image information; if yes, combining a Zhang Zhengyou calibration method with an RTK technology and a PID technology to park the unmanned aerial vehicle to be landed; and if not, stopping the parking of the to-be-landed unmanned aerial vehicle. column12: Cable hunting method and device based on Faraday's electromagnetic induction law
column13: The invention relates to the field of the power, and especially relates to a cable hunting method and device based on Faraday's electromagnetic induction law. The method comprises the following steps:producing induction current different from the original current frequency on a to-be-hunted cable; respectively measuring the induction current produced on the to-be-hunted cable and the induction current on each output cable; and judging that the output cable and the to-be-hunted cable is the same cable if the difference between the induction current produced on one output cable and the induction current on the to-be-hunted cable is less than a threshold., The following effects can be realized by using the method disclosed by the invention: the same cable can be found by measuring the induction current with close size in the output cable through a measurement module as long as the induction current is produced on a shielding layer ground line through an open-closes current transformer, and the hunting is convenient and fast.

column12: SYSTEM MODULE OF SIMULATING MACHINE OPERATION SCREEN BASED ON NON-INVASIVE DATA-EXTRACTION SYSTEM
column13: A system module applied to the machine controller for simulating a machine operation screen based on a non-invasive data-extraction system, is disclosed. An image capture device of the system module can receive an original operation screen outputted from the machine controller, and transmit the original operation screen to the non-invasive data-extraction system and a high-speed image process unit for extraction of the information shown on the operation screen. The software control system can extract the operational information of the machine controller in real time, to create a machine operation flow for generating a simulated machine operation screen which is then outputted to a screen of the machine controller. As a result, the site working staff can be provided with operational information associated with the machine in real time, for example, the operational information includes currently executed operation screen, position of mouse cursor and pop-up window detection result.

column12: Foundation bolt fixer
column13: The utility model relates to the technical field of foundation bolt embedding, in particular to a foundation bolt fixer, which comprises a horizontal positioning mechanism and a longitudinal elevation adjusting mechanism arranged below the horizontal positioning mechanism. The horizontal positioning mechanism comprises a rectangular bottom frame composed of an X-axis direction sliding rail and a connecting rod and a Y-axis direction positioning clamping groove formed in the rectangular bottom frame, and X-axis scales are arranged on the X-axis direction sliding rail. The two ends of the Y-axis direction positioning clamping groove are connected with the X-axis direction sliding rails through locking mechanisms respectively, a long hole is formed in the Y-axis direction positioning clamping groove, and Y-axis scales are arranged on the two sides of the long hole respectively. The longitudinal elevation adjusting mechanism comprises a sleeve and a telescopic rod arranged in the sleeve, and the sleeve is connected with the telescopic rod through a locking mechanism. Double positioning of the position and the elevation of the foundation bolt is achieved, the accuracy of the embedded position of the foundation bolt is improved, the foundation bolt can be directly detached after being fixed to the foundation column, and the utilization rate is high.

column12: Light-control water-cooling thyristor monitoring protection circuit
column13: The utility model relates to a light-control water-cooling thyristor monitoring protection circuit which has the voltage class of 6kV-66kV and above, and is used for heat dissipation by water-cooling. The circuit comprises an energy taking and sampling circuit, a voltage-stabilizing circuit, a control circuit, a pulse circuit, an energy accumulating circuit, a driving circuit and a laser emission head, wherein the two ends of a thyristor are connected with the energy taking and sampling circuit which is respectively connected with the voltage-stabilizing circuit and the control circuit; the voltage-stabilizing circuit is respectively connected with the energy accumulating circuit and the control circuit; the energy accumulating circuit is respectively connected with the pulse circuit and the driving circuit; the pulse circuit is also respectively connected with the control circuit and the driving circuit; and the driving circuit is connected with the laser emission head. The light-control water-cooling thyristor monitoring protection circuit has the advantages that by adopting the working way of instantaneous short energy accumulation and discharge of a pulse sampling circuit, the light-control water-cooling thyristor monitoring protection circuit has higher work stability and anti-interference property, simple and reliable circuit, extremely low energy consumption, good output wave form and long working life.

column12: Automatic power generation control method and device based on bidding auxiliary service market
column13: The invention relates to an automatic power generation control method based on a bidding auxiliary service market, and belongs to the technical field of automatic power generation control. The methodcomprises the steps of determining a regional adjustment demand according to a current period of a unit and a current interval of an ACE value of a power grid; according to a preset limit value type,the regional adjustment requirement and a quotation interval table obtained according to the quotation sequence table of each power plant, determining an adjustment gear of unit output under the limitvalue type and a unit participating in adjustment; and calculating the unit output instruction value according to the adjusting gear, issuing the instruction value to the unit participating in adjustment, and enabling the unit participating in adjustment to execute the instruction value. In consideration of different periods of a heat supply period and a non-heat supply period, a dynamic upper and lower limit mode is newly added on the basis of original AGC remote measurement upper and lower limits and static upper and lower limits; providing a plurality of sets of dynamic control limit values, and calculating an active instruction value of each unit controller. The bidding quotation and fairness principle is considered, and the auxiliary service market is optimized.

column12: Large-scale high-bearing long-service-life maintainable sun-oriented driving mechanism and operation method
column13: The invention provides a large-scale high-load-bearing long-service-life maintainable sun-oriented driving mechanism and an operation method. The large-scale high-load-bearing long-service-life maintainable sun-oriented driving mechanism comprises a composite material main structure, a cabin body interface flange, a truss interface flange, a wrapping tape locking and releasing assembly, a rotary supporting device and a driving and locking assembly. The composite material main structure is connected with a cabin body interface flange; the cabin body interface flange provides a spacecraft cabin body connecting interface; the truss interface flange provides an outboard load connection interface; the wrapping tape locking and releasing assembly hoops the composite material main structure and the truss interface flange on the launching section and releases the composite material main structure and the truss interface flange on the rail section. The rotation supporting device supports the truss interface flange and provides rotation freedom degree for the truss interface flange on the on-orbit section. The driving locking assembly serves as a power source to drive the truss interface flange to rotate. The invention has the advantages of strong bearing capacity of a launching section, large driving capacity of an on-orbit section, strong braking capacity, high transmission power, long service life and on-orbit maintainability, and is suitable for a high-power long-service-life spacecraft platform.

column13: The utility model discloses an efficient production device for waste asphalt powder-based green cementing material concrete. column12: Green power index calculation method and system
column13: The invention relates to a green power index calculation method and system, and the method is characterized in that the method comprises the steps: determining the comprehensive evaluation data of a to-be-evaluated region and a plurality of regions; according to the comprehensive evaluation data of the to-be-evaluated area and the comprehensive evaluation data of the plurality of areas, homogenizing the comprehensive evaluation data of the to-be-evaluated area and the comprehensive evaluation data of the plurality of areas, and determining weights of the comprehensive evaluation data of the to-be-evaluated area and the comprehensive evaluation data of the plurality of areas; according to the comprehensive evaluation data of the to-be-evaluated area and the plurality of areas and the corresponding weights thereof, green power indexes of the to-be-evaluated area and the plurality of areas are respectively determined, transverse comparison is carried out, the green power index degree of the to-be-evaluated area is determined, and the method can be widely applied to the field of green power.

column12: Flood prevention consultation monitoring device and method based on Internet of Things
column13: The invention discloses a flood prevention consultation monitoring device and method based on the Internet of Things, relates to the technical field of flood prevention consultation monitoring, and solves the technical problem that the flood prevention accuracy is reduced due to the fact that regional analysis cannot be performed in the prior art.A region analysis unit is used for carrying out region division on the monitoring region and analyzing the divided regions; the geographical environment of each region is analyzed, the flood prevention accuracy is improved, and the monitoring error is reduced; an early warning signal is generated according to the current environment, so that heavy loss caused by flood due to the fact that the early warning signal is not timely is prevented; the regional analysis is verified, so that the accuracy of the regional data of the database is improved, and early warning errors caused by data exception are prevented; danger signals of different levels are generated according to river analysis, and the influence of flood is judged through real-time data, so that early warning measures of the same level are reasonably matched, the early warning efficiency is effectively improved, and the output cost of early warning is reduced.

column12: Database abnormal behavior detection method and device
column13: The invention provides a database abnormal behavior detection method and device. The method comprises the steps of obtaining a database log data set; performing sliding processing on each log by utilizing a fixed window, and extracting contents of three fields of SQL (Structured Query Language) statement, running time and operation time in each window as a sliding window database behavior sample, so as to obtain a sliding window database behavior data set; encoding SQL statements and operation time of each sliding window database behavior sample in the sliding window database behavior data set to form a sliding window database behavior sample matrix, and summing the matrix according to columns to obtain a sliding window database behavior vector data set; and normalizing the sliding window database behavior vector data set, and inputting the normalized sliding window database behavior vector data set into a pre-trained DAGMM database abnormal behavior detection model to obtain a detection result. According to the method, the problems of single SQL statement detection vulnerabilities and manual data annotation in the previous database abnormal behavior detection research are well solved.

column12: Electrical Components Having Metal Traces With Protected Sidewalls
column13: A component such as a display may have a substrate and thin-film circuitry on the substrate. The thin-film circuitry may be used to form an array of pixels for a display or other circuit structures. Metal traces may be formed among dielectric layers in the thin-film circuitry. Metal traces may be provided with insulating protective sidewall structures. The protective sidewall structures may be formed by treating exposed edge surfaces of the metal traces. A metal trace may have multiple layers such as a core metal layer sandwiched between barrier metal layers. The core metal layer may be formed from a metal that is subject to corrosion. The protective sidewall structures may help prevent corrosion in the core metal layer. Surface treatments such as oxidation, nitridation, and other processes may be used in forming the protective sidewall structures.

column12: Dynamic reactive power compensation device with grading and shielding rings
column13: The utility model relates to a dynamic reactive power compensation device with grading and shielding rings. A single-phase thyristor valve block is formed by connecting a plurality of valve units in series; each valve unit comprises a thyristor unit, a RC protection unit, a return unit, an internal water pipe unit, and an internal cable trough; and grading and shielding rings are arranged outside the frameworks at the upper end and the lower end of each unit. The grading and shielding rings adopt continuous ring-shaped structures, and supported beams are fixed in the middle of the ring-shaped structures. The utility model has the advantages of good proportionality of the valve block-to-ground electric field, flash over, self-discharge phenomenon avoidance, can ensure safe and stable operation of the thyristor valve, and improve the reliability of the dynamic reactive power compensation device.

column12: Underwater engineering anti-condensation structure and construction method
column13: The invention provides an underwater engineering anti-condensation structure. The underwater engineering anti-condensation structure comprises an underwater engineering wall surface and an underwater engineering ground surface, wherein a plurality of flow guide grooves are formed in the surface layers of the underwater engineering wall surface and the underwater engineering ground surface; integrated wall plates are further mounted on the outer sides of the flow guide grooves in the underwater engineering wall surface and the underwater engineering ground surface; and a system water collecting pit for collecting condensation water is further formed in one side of each flow guide groove. column12: Power monitoring system operation and maintenance behavior security threat assessment method and equipment
column13: The invention discloses a power monitoring system operation and maintenance behavior security threat assessment method and equipment. The method comprises the following steps: converting operation and maintenance transaction attributes recorded by an operation and maintenance log to obtain a numeralized operation and maintenance transaction feature set; performing operation and maintenance role classification on operation and maintenance transactions in the operation and maintenance transaction feature set; in each type of operation and maintenance role, calculating a personnel portrait deviation score according to the deviation between the operation and maintenance affair and the personnel portrait characteristic attribute of the operation and maintenance role; in each type of operation and maintenance role, obtaining an abnormal instruction behavior score according to a detection result of the integrated learning anomaly detection model; and determining a total behavior score according to the personnel portrait deviation score and the abnormal instruction behavior score, and determining the security threat level of the operation and maintenance affair according to a preset relationship between the behavior score and the security threat level. The method has the advantages that high detection accuracy can be obtained; in combination with related principles of ensemble learning, the advantages of various different detection methods can be combined to obtain a better threat detection effect.

column12: Network intrusion detection method and system
column13: The invention discloses a network intrusion detection method which is characterized by comprising the following steps: arranging intercepted network data packets to obtain a network data set; performing feature engineering processing on the network data set to obtain a network detection data set; performing dimensionality reduction on the network detection data set by adopting the trained denoising self-encoding neural network model; adopting the trained XGBoost network intrusion detection model to carry out intrusion detection on the network detection data after dimension reduction; constructing an intrusion database for the intruded network data and the disclosed intrusion data according to the detection result; regularly retraining the de-noising self-encoding neural network model and the XGBoost network intrusion detection model according to the intrusion database, and performing intrusion detection on the network data according to the retrained model. Compared with the prior art, the network intrusion data are detected more accurately.

column13: The invention relates to the technical field of hydrological supervision, solves the problem that an existing hydrological monitoring system cannot deeply analyze the relevance of polluted areas, and particularly relates to a hydrological monitoring feedback system based on 5G and Beidou technologies, which comprises a monitoring platform in communication connection with an acquisition module, a water level analysis module, a water quality analysis module and a storage module. column13: The utility model discloses an active lubricating device for a fan speed reducer of a spray cooling tower, and belongs to the field of speed reducer lubricating devices. The device comprises a speed reducer, a diaphragm pump and an oil storage tank, the diaphragm pump and the oil storage tank are arranged outside the spray cooling tower, the oil storage tank is a closed box body with a transparent window on the side surface, an upper oil inlet and a lower oil inlet of the speed reducer are respectively connected with an outlet on one side of the diaphragm pump through three-way valves, and an upper oil outlet and a lower oil outlet of the speed reducer are respectively connected with an inlet on the other side of the diaphragm pump through three-way valves; and the other two pipe orifices of the diaphragm pump are respectively led into the oil storage tank through pipelines. column12: Transformer area line loss calculation method and system, storage medium and calculation equipment
column13: The invention discloses a transformer area line loss calculation method. The method comprises the steps that acquiring transformer area total power, transformer area phase line current, transformer area phase line voltage and transformer area neutral line current collected by a power terminal side; calculating the active power of each section of the phase line, the reactive power of each section of the phase line, the resistance of each section of the phase line, the active power of each section of the neutral line, the reactive power of each section of the neutral line and the resistance of each section of the neutral line; calculating the line loss of each phase line and the line loss of a neutral line in the transformer area; and calculating the line loss of the transformer area. Meanwhile, the invention discloses a corresponding system, a storage medium and computing equipment. According to the method, the line loss of each line is calculated by adopting the split-phase line, the line loss of the transformer area is calculated through the line loss of each line, and compared with a traditional calculation method, the accuracy is higher.

column12: Capacitance online monitoring method and device for low-frequency power transmission matrix converter
column13: The invention provides a capacitor online monitoring method and device for a low-frequency power transmission matrix converter, and the method comprises the steps: collecting the current voltage of a to-be-monitored capacitor, and collecting a voltage signal and a current signal at two ends of a commutation chain where the to-be-monitored capacitor is located; respectively inputting the voltage signal and the current signal into a wave trap to obtain a first alternating voltage, a first alternating current, a second alternating voltage and a second alternating current; obtaining a first power factor angle according to the first AC voltage and the first AC current, obtaining a second power factor angle according to the second AC voltage and the second AC current, and obtaining a phase angle difference between the first AC voltage and the second AC voltage; determining a real-time capacitance value according to a calculation formula by combining the voltage average value of the to-be-monitored capacitor in a preset time period; and when the real-time capacitance value is reduced to a preset limit value, judging that the to-be-monitored capacitor is aged. The capacitance value is calculated on line based on the circuit structure relation of the M3C converter, and normal operation and control of the M3C converter are not affected.

column12: Pouring formwork structure for V-shaped inclined column
column13: The pouring formwork structure is used for pouring construction of a column body, the column body comprises a vertical column and an inclined column, the inclined column and the vertical column are connected to form a V-shaped structure, the pouring formwork structure comprises a supporting frame and a formwork structure, the formwork structure is arranged on the outer side of the column body, the supporting frame is arranged on the outer side of the formwork structure, and the supporting frame is arranged on the outer side of the formwork structure. The support frame is erected on the ground; the formwork structure comprises an inner side formwork, an outer side formwork and splicing formworks, the outer side formwork is arranged on the outer side of the V-shaped structure, the inner side formwork is arranged on the inner side of the V-shaped structure, and the splicing formworks are arranged on the front side and the rear side of the V-shaped structure. The formwork structure is divided into three parts, the number of the formworks is reduced, the sizes of the formworks are guaranteed, the formworks can be conveniently erected, meanwhile, after a small number of formworks are spliced, the structure is more stable, the forming effect on a column is better, the forming quality of the column is guaranteed, and meanwhile the construction period is shortened.

column12: Quick connection node for steel bars of stiff beam column
column13: The utility model discloses a stiff beam column reinforcing steel bar fast connecting node which comprises a base, a connecting base is arranged in the middle of the upper end of the base, a steel column is arranged in the middle of the upper end of the connecting base, clamping grooves are formed in the left end and the right end of the steel column, and adjusting assemblies are arranged in the two clamping grooves. The ends, away from the steel column, of the two adjusting assemblies are each provided with a connecting device, the left portion and the right portion of the upper end of the base are each provided with a set of fixing bolts, a connecting groove is formed in the middle of the upper end of the connecting base, and reinforcing bolts are arranged in the middle of the front end and the middle of the rear end of the connecting base. According to the quick connecting joint for the steel bars of the stiff beam column, the connecting base and the connecting equipment are arranged, the steel column is connected into the connecting groove and reinforced through the reinforcing bolts, the connecting base is connected to the base, the base is fixed through the fixing bolts, and therefore stability is improved; the steel bars are convenient to connect.

column12: H-shaped cast steel joint for crack control of super-long structure
column13: The utility model discloses an H-shaped cast steel node for controlling cracks of a super-long structure, which comprises a main body, a connecting frame arranged on the left portion of the front end of the main body, a first fixing plate arranged on the left side of the front end of the main body, a connecting plate arranged at the left end of the main body, and supporting plates arranged on the right portion of the front end and the right portion of the rear end of the main body. Connecting grooves are formed in the right portion of the upper end and the right portion of the lower end of the main body, a vertical base is arranged at the right end of the connecting plate, a containing groove is formed in the right end of the vertical base, reinforcing bolts are arranged at the front end and the rear end of the vertical base, and the main body and the connecting plate are connected together through the vertical base. According to the novel H-shaped cast steel joint for controlling the ultra-long structure crack, the connecting frame and the first fixing plate are arranged, the connecting column and the connecting shaft are arranged, so that the connecting frame and the first fixing plate are conveniently connected to the main body, the connecting plate is fixed to the left end of the vertical base through the reinforcing bolt, and the supporting plate is connected to the main body through the supporting rod; therefore, the forming efficiency is improved.

column12: Insulator shielding cover for power distribution operation
column13: The utility model relates to an insulator shielding cover for power distribution operation, which comprises a body and an insulating operating rod, three support mounting grooves are uniformly arranged on the upper side and the lower side of the upper surface of the body from left to right, isolation plate clamping grooves are arranged between the support mounting grooves on the upper side and the lower side of the upper surface of the body, and second support sections are arranged in the support mounting grooves. One end of each second support section is provided with a first support section in the vertical direction, the middle of the top of each first support section is provided with an open groove, the left side and the right side of the top of each first support section are provided with a universal ball and a clamping protrusion respectively, wire clamps are arranged above the first support sections, and connecting ball grooves are formed in the positions, corresponding to the universal balls, of the lower ends of the left sides of the wire clamps. Clamping grooves are formed in the positions, corresponding to the clamping protrusions, of the lower end of the wire clamp, and wire clamping blocks are arranged in the positions, corresponding to the open grooves, of the middle of the lower end of the wire clamp; the device has the advantages of being convenient and fast to use, high in working efficiency and high in safety coefficient.

column12: Super-long inverted triangular arc-shaped pipe truss structure
column13: The utility model discloses a super-long inverted triangle arc-shaped pipe truss structure which comprises a low-area bearing stand column, a high-area bearing stand column, a truss, a low-area spherical hinge seat and a high-area spherical hinge seat, the low-area spherical hinge seat is directly welded on the low-area bearing stand column after being welded with a first rear-cut locking and stacking plate in advance, and the high-area spherical hinge seat is directly welded on the high-area bearing stand column after being welded with a second rear-cut locking and stacking plate in advance. column12: Cutting device
column13: The utility model provides a cutting device, which belongs to the technical field of pipeline cutting and comprises a cutting knife, a cutting knife support, a clamping component, an elastic componentand a threaded rod. The cutting knife bracket comprises a first mounting part and a second mounting part which are oppositely arranged, and a connecting part for connecting the first mounting part and the second mounting part; the cutting knife is installed on the first installation part, the clamping part is installed on the connecting part in a sliding mode, and a pipe fitting clamping space isformed by the cutting knife and the clamping part. A threaded hole is formed in the second mounting part, the threaded rod is mounted on the second mounting part through the threaded hole, and one end of the threaded rod points to the clamping part; an elastic component is arranged at the end, close to the clamping component, of the threaded rod and abuts against the side, away from the pipe fitting, of the clamping component. According to the cutting device provided by the utility model, the distance between the pipe wall and the cutting knife is automatically adjusted in the cutting processof the pipe fitting, so that the cutting knife can uninterruptedly cut the pipe fitting, and the cutting efficiency is improved.
